: "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7572": {"changesets": [{"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1381520 - Stop making duplicated builds on beta for win{32,64} + mac r=Callek a=release CLOSED TREE\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GapZxnGFCvq", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/target_tasks.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2b7b0fd96fcedec7bcdebd81d185118b96a4a60d", "parents": ["68b791c2971af37c17ed9b1903302fb58f3be938"], "tags": []}], "date": 1501841809, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jlorenzo@mozilla.com"}, "7573": {"changesets": [{"author": "Philipp Kewisch \u003cphilipp@bugzilla.kewis.ch\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b1_2017080501_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1387524 - Back out removal of MOZ_PRETTY to build Thunderbird 56 beta. a=jorgk\n\nBackout most of changeset 318f1bcd336e from bug 1329355 to support building releases on buildbot.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: K4QAA8IIpVX", "files": ["toolkit/locales/l10n.mk", "toolkit/mozapps/installer/package-name.mk"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7a172bce1a933689179ec584f2273855748030e1", "parents": ["2b7b0fd96fcedec7bcdebd81d185118b96a4a60d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b1_2017080501_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1385905 - part2: HTMLEditRules::SplitParagraph() should insert normal \u003cbr\u003e element rather than moz-\u003cbr\u003e element if split element and/or new element is empty r=m_kato a=jorgk\n\nCurrently, HTMLEditRules::SplitParagraph() inserts moz-\u003cbr\u003e element when split element and/or new element causes empty line.  However, PlaintextSerializer ignores moz-\u003cbr\u003e elements.  Therefore, empty lines which are created by SplitParagraph() will be removed when it's converted to plaintext.\n\nSo, it should insert normal \u003cbr\u003e element for placeholder of empty lines instead.  Note that moz-\u003cbr\u003e elements are appeared as normal \u003cbr\u003e elements in the result of Element.innerHTML.  Additionally, Chromium always inserts a \u003cbr\u003e element for empty block elements which are created by Enter key press.  Therefore, using normal \u003cbr\u003e element in this case shouldn't cause any compatibility problems.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FNV41zEFWqQ", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.h", "editor/libeditor/TextEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/TextEditRules.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "395cb2c77448f9d3f305a189c191c7c6c360844b", "parents": ["7a172bce1a933689179ec584f2273855748030e1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b1_2017080501_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1350152 - Don't rely on gBrowser in nsLoginManagerPrompter.js. r=mkaply a=jorgk DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE\n\nIn bug 1266836 we fixed this code to properly work in e10s,\nbut made the mistake of using gBrowser in toolkit code, breaking\nXUL apps that don't have a gBrowser. This solution implements\na different code-path for non-e10s and returns a chrome\nwindow for consumers that don't offer a browser.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 929ahDenzu5", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/nsLoginManagerPrompter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "74e49a52007c609495c6cbc673487ed457838d9e", "parents": ["395cb2c77448f9d3f305a189c191c7c6c360844b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1501938180, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "mozilla@jorgk.com"}, "7574": {"changesets": [{"author": "Yoshi Huang \u003callstars.chh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1340974 - To make data-url.html pass. r=smaug, a=test-only\n\nThe original test in [1] will throw Syntax error, due to we strip whitespace in\n[2]. The test 'else postMessage(..)' will become 'elsepostMessage(...)'\nand cause ReferenceError: elsepostMessage is not defined. So I added {}\nto fix the error.\n\nAlso in the last test [3], it will trigger error handler in the testing\nframework, and the TestHarness will fail if there's an error thrown. So I\nadded 'setup({allow_uncaught_exception:true});' to fix this.\n\n[1]: http://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/f0e4ae5f8c40ba742214e89aba3f554da0b89a33/testing/web-platform/tests/workers/data-url.html#53\n[2]: http://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/f0e4ae5f8c40ba742214e89aba3f554da0b89a33/netwerk/protocol/data/nsDataHandler.cpp#92\n[3]: http://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/f0e4ae5f8c40ba742214e89aba3f554da0b89a33/testing/web-platform/tests/workers/data-url.html#56", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/workers/data-url.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/tests/workers/data-url.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "58a56b524b5ec309371c0e1e1313f813c0b83344", "parents": ["2b7b0fd96fcedec7bcdebd81d185118b96a4a60d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1316770 - Add text-rendering:optimizeLegibility to reftests for bug 1089388, to try and ensure we get proper glyph bounds. r=gbrown, a=test-only", "files": ["layout/reftests/writing-mode/1089388-1-ref.html", "layout/reftests/writing-mode/1089388-1.html", "layout/reftests/writing-mode/1089388-2-ref.html", "layout/reftests/writing-mode/1089388-2.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c4b95f208eeb55003dbbe7da141e2a995cd4bbcb", "parents": ["58a56b524b5ec309371c0e1e1313f813c0b83344"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kate Ustiuzhanina \u003ckustiuzhanina@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1385417 - Fix sendOnTimeout test. r=gfritzsche, a=test-only", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetryHealthPing.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4923833da3f914e9453fc14feebab00cca320509", "parents": ["c4b95f208eeb55003dbbe7da141e2a995cd4bbcb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Layzell \u003cmichael@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1353264 - Disable testing native stack collection in Beta. r=froydnj, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4Ssxa3iUcHK", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_ThreadHangStats.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b4cf744da12607de4dda7830dd7a7114de84606", "parents": ["4923833da3f914e9453fc14feebab00cca320509"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Geoff Brown \u003cgbrown@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1361476 - Run linux64-asan/opt mochitest-devtools-chrome tests on xlarge instances, experimentally. r=jmaher, a=test-only\n\nChange from 'legacy' to 'xlarge' instances for these tests to see if they run more reliably over the long term.\nIf they do run more reliably, we should consider upgrading other asan mochitests; if not, we should back this out.", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/test/tests.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5fb77be6beb6a24a25e618a4e194446a91679f5a", "parents": ["3b4cf744da12607de4dda7830dd7a7114de84606"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Justin Wood \u003cCallek@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1386079 - Disable gtest on windows nightly, it is permafailing because we PGO nightlies. r=jlorenzo, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2dCMfPnpeg4", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/test/tests.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "43de028e27603290050eb17828d0dd24ea39381b", "parents": ["5fb77be6beb6a24a25e618a4e194446a91679f5a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387263 - Rewrite test case to remove possible race condition. r=jandem, a=test-only", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/basic/testBug756919.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c153cf4c08d6a53390e4ce936acba0114b065c68", "parents": ["43de028e27603290050eb17828d0dd24ea39381b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kingston \u003cjkt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1325902 - Move container tab highlight from test pilot ex