ires. r=karlt, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3vva2XgSa60", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f592e9f5e8d2a578a8e54e91514ec3e1124150a0", "parents": ["b304b54bb8c6056bd76c2af1edc9aaa0bff03de1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387190 - Fire \"input\" event for \u003cselect\u003e and datetime \u003cinput\u003e. r=esawin, a=gchang\n\nFire \"input\" event in addition to \"change\" event for both \u003cselect\u003e\nfields and date/time \u003cinput\u003e fields.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8UDdF8ZnM2e", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/content/InputWidgetHelper.js", "mobile/android/chrome/content/SelectHelper.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c23f9c735d299160f9df8d2a5ab0838562f4e013", "parents": ["f592e9f5e8d2a578a8e54e91514ec3e1124150a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "steveck-chung \u003cschung@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1386959 - [Form Autofill] Add probe for form autofill availability. r=francois, r=lchang, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KPOBxmHOiuK", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/bootstrap.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "72f3e9b7c6ea3cbd5edf816ef3a30c3f5595a219", "parents": ["c23f9c735d299160f9df8d2a5ab0838562f4e013"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1380824 - Call RepaintSelection out of script blocker. r=masayuki, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LFyZLW0da7f", "files": ["editor/libeditor/EditorBase.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6562cd359748066a9733b8aafe017097985f5006", "parents": ["72f3e9b7c6ea3cbd5edf816ef3a30c3f5595a219"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kevin Hsieh \u003ckevin.hsieh@ucla.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1325080 - Synchronously decode image metadata for data URIs. r=tnikkel, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IPrP3EepQ6a", "files": ["image/ImageFactory.cpp", "image/test/mochitest/mochitest.ini", "image/test/mochitest/test_bug1325080.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ccef81da61b21be6ada2fc975550c9ec064165f4", "parents": ["6562cd359748066a9733b8aafe017097985f5006"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393883 - Update follow-on search add-on to 0.9.3. r=past, a=gchang", "files": ["browser/extensions/followonsearch/content/followonsearch-fs.js", "browser/extensions/followonsearch/install.rdf"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2ccccb08ff4b67df307d9403962efc9be0a323a6", "parents": ["ccef81da61b21be6ada2fc975550c9ec064165f4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1503926362, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7684": {"changesets": [{"author": "angelsl \u003cangelsl@in04.sg\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1324499 - Save and restore scroll position after reflow in GetContentSizeInternal. r=dbaron, a=gchang\n\nThe bug is caused by the first call to ResizeReflow in\nnsDocumentViewer::GetContentSizeInternal, which reflows the content with\nunlimited height. ResizeReflow calls DidDoReflow, which calls a\ncallback installed by nsHTMLScrollFrame that clamps the scroll port setting\nthe scroll top to 0 and losing the original scroll top. When the content\nis reflowed again to the maximum height, the scroll top stays at 0.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3VkgWLqSTDP", "files": ["layout/base/nsDocumentViewer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cb753cf67c6cc92f7fa26b7128656b731cc114b7", "parents": ["2ccccb08ff4b67df307d9403962efc9be0a323a6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390088 - Part 1: Change the type of the parameter of nsSVGLength2::GetAnimValue from \"SVGSVGElement*\" to \"SVGViewportElement*\" r=jwatt, a=gchang\n\nThere are two overloads of nsSVGLength2::GetAnimValue:\n\n1. float nsSVGLength2::GetAnimValue(nsSVGElement*) const;\n2. float nsSVGLength2::GetAnimValue(SVGSVGElement*) const;\n\nIn Bug 265894, I created SVGViewportElement as a base class of SVGSVGElement.\nSVGSVGElement::GetViewBoxTransform was moved to SVGViewportElement in that\nrefactoring. The local variable 'ctx' in that function was changed from\nSVGSVGElement to SVGViewportElement, which when passed to\nnsSVGLength2::GetAnimValue caused us to switch from calling the overload that\ntakes a SVGSVGElement to the overload that takes a nsSVGElement, which is not\nwhat we want.\n\nThis patch changes the argument type of the nsSVGLength2::GetAnimValue overload\nthat takes an SVGSVGElement to take an SVGViewportElement instead, which causes\nthe GetAnimValue(ctx) calls in SVGViewportElement::GetViewBoxTransform to call\nthe correct GetAnimValue overload again.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2cmgIoltYfY", "files": ["dom/svg/nsSVGLength2.cpp", "dom/svg/nsSVGLength2.h", "layout/svg/nsSVGGradientFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6dc06b2e7ed1e3a7542be7d4564e7e826eee0a67", "parents": ["cb753cf67c6cc92f7fa26b7128656b731cc114b7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390088 - Part 2: Add a reftest to check percentage width/height on inner-\u003csvg\u003e resolves against the nearest \u003csvg\u003e ancestor. r=jwatt, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KmWd9kMx8j3", "files": ["layout/reftests/svg/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/svg/svg-in-inner-svg-dimensions.svg"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "03ac0153495de76493287deb99f57ec6b4677ed9", "parents": ["6dc06b2e7ed1e3a7542be7d4564e7e826eee0a67"], "tags": []}, {"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390088 - Part 3: Declare some locale nsSVGLength2 references as const in nsSVGOuterSVGFrame.cpp. r=jwatt, a=gchang\n\nThis patch has no direct relation with this bug. When tracing the code, I noticed\nthose local nsSVGLength2 variables can be declared as const reference.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6gkdlpv8W7H", "files": ["layout/svg/nsSVGOuterSVGFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b7c7741c9be57eccb4db837a8ce4bfbe4a873bf9", "parents": ["03ac0153495de76493287deb99f57ec6b4677ed9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390097 - Revert a part of bug 1354020 changes. r=masayuki, a=gchang\n\nBug 1354020 causes that IMM-IME on Windows 7 doesn't work with --no-remote.  Although I think that this issue is OS or IME bug, when default window proceduce by RegisterClass is DefaultWindowProcW, Google Japanese IME doesn't work.\n\nI am not sure why this issue occurs when lpfnWndProc is DefWidnowProcW and DDE isn't started.  But for workaround, we should revert a part of bug 1354020 changes.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BkxlZnm8mIh", "files": ["widget/windows/WinUtils.cpp", "widget/windows/WinUtils.h", "widget/windows/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f2c71d60be697de4380ca8b776aa346ff57e0f60", "parents": ["b7c7741c9be57eccb4db837a8ce4bfbe4a873bf9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ray Lin \u003cralin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391791 - Calculate controlBar width without counting toward audio padding. r=jaws, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DHuUef5R2VN", "files": ["toolkit/content/tests/reftests/audio-height-with-padding-ref.html", "toolkit/content/tests/reftests/audio-height-with-padding.html", "toolkit/content/tests/reftests/audio-with-padding-ref.html", "toolkit/content/tests/reftests/audio-with-padding.html", "toolkit/content/tests/reftests/reftest.list", "toolkit/content/widgets/videocontrols.xml", "toolkit/themes/shared/media/videocontrols.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ae11b062cb40d3d5779190dbe122fb5c2064ea4", "parents": ["f2c71d60be697de4380ca8b776aa346ff57e0f60"], "tags": []}, {"author": "k88hudson \u003ckhudson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393148 - Hide Topics component if no topics available in Activity Stream. r=Mardak, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1WgTeCkrs58", "files": ["browser/extensions/activity-stream/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5ade015bbd6d2327d6679220bb81b7b2ecb160d3", "parents": ["0ae11b062cb40d3d5779190dbe122fb5c2064ea4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1389718 - Fix receiving a message in proxy sandbox when running OOP. r=kmag, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: xgHIph36SG", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionParent.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-common.ini", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "36a40a9290b8976e7c3e9c2b60686161b7911b7f", "parents": ["5ade015bbd6d2327d6679220bb81b7b2ecb160d3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390140 - Account for bookmark ID being \u003cnull\u003e when populating BrowserSearch's HomeContextMenuInfo. r=Grisha, a=gchang\n\nThe combined history view returns a bookmark ID of \u003cnull\u003e for items that aren't a bookmark. Calling cursor.getInt() silently turns this into an ID of 0, which doesn't play well with the rest of our code that assumes that the bookmark ID for items that aren't in fact bookmarks is -1.\n\nWhen pressing \"Remove\" on a search history result, this means that we then end up trying to remove bookmark 0, i.e. the root \"bookmark\". Luckily this attempt doesn't succeed, but unfortunately still manages to crash the browser along the way.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FZk4cI2EDAE", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/home/BrowserSearch.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f1e924b5acd9996fdd28b27eb1ab5d28978d0e1", "parents": ["36a40a9290b8976e7c3e9c2b60686161b7911b7f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ricky Chien \u003cricky060709@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392873 - Fix missing all-tabs-menu when detaching devtools to a separate window. r=Honza, a=gchang", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/toolsidebar.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/src/components/tabbox-panel.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/tabs/tabbar.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec2c40638986c673ec390dccd64c8337fd312ba2", "parents": ["1f1e924b5acd9996fdd28b27eb1ab5d28978d0e1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1503928521, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7685": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nbr -\u003e 0c692a161e6a\nes-AR -\u003e 63e6fd7fd0d7\nfa -\u003e d352c27cb418\nfi -\u003e 0cea56079961\nhu -\u003e 4eef43d685ea\nnl -\u003e 5676db0716a9\nrm -\u003e 6b8e6367d9d0\nsk -\u003e 8434673d6af8\ntr -\u003e 62966e6ad370", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "53dc3cc7dba64775b91585a03f87a371372cfc62", "parents": ["ec2c40638986c673ec390dccd64c8337fd312ba2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1503932427, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7686": {"changesets": [{"author": "Alessio Placitelli \u003calessio.placitelli@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335236 - Fix intermittent test_TelemetrySend.js due to flaky time tests. r=chutten, a=test-only\n\nOn very fast builds (OPT, PGO) this test can fail intermittently because the time it takes to send a ping and receive a reply is 0. Account for that by replacing all the \"greater than\" checks with \"greater or equal than\".\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JvEo2rCbJj6", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetrySend.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fe81d9af21d6fd8e0c5882079162a591e07ab680", "parents": ["53dc3cc7dba64775b91585a03f87a371372cfc62"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wood \u003crwood@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387377 - Don't run gtest or awsy on devedition builds. r=jmaher, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2siiOBftTYs", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/test/tests.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "67363a144710b4f2466dc6836c066707bacb5a88", "parents": ["fe81d9af21d6fd8e0c5882079162a591e07ab680"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eitan Isaacson \u003ceitan@monotonous.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387918 - Retrieve current array for owner in aria owns hash table. r=surkov, a=jcristau", "files": ["accessible/generic/DocAccessible.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fe5af9d9fdb24c25b59f796b13c1070c9f41cfd1", "parents": ["67363a144710b4f2466dc6836c066707bacb5a88"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1340425 - Add back the magic GC in DoShutdown() to avoid intermittent leaks. r=smaug, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CNkjPk9FLKj", "files": ["toolkit/xre/nsXREDirProvider.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cb236dfdd7bbffb31d9fc33e22d9645f768f9a42", "parents": ["fe5af9d9fdb24c25b59f796b13c1070c9f41cfd1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "steveck-chung \u003cschung@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390816 - Part 2: Add browser test for sync enabled case. r=lchang, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FpsaoaMc6U4", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/test/browser/browser_first_time_use_doorhanger.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/browser/browser_submission_in_private_mode.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/browser/browser_update_doorhanger.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2c15a6ed11f7912081bd7e029fab8ddfb2b41145", "parents": ["cb236dfdd7bbffb31d9fc33e22d9645f768f9a42"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ray Lin \u003cralin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388152 - Save abbreviated state name of address-level1 select element rather than its value in form autofill submission. r=lchang, r=MattN, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IjZKzEdLlq5", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillHandler.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillUtils.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_onFormSubmitted.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8b4fbaa0a0de8752ec212789f465eb62ca17f3b9", "parents": ["2c15a6ed11f7912081bd7e029fab8ddfb2b41145"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391770 - Don't allow a faraway second tap to start a one-touch-pinch gesture. r=botond, a=lizzard\n\nThis patch adds a new tolerance pref, which controls how far the second touchdown\nis allowed to be from the first touchdown when detecting a multi-tap gesture\nsuch as double-tap or one-touch-pinch. This stops the one-touch-pinch code\nfrom inadvertently triggering when the user does a tap followed by a second tap\nfar away from the first.\n\nThe default value for the new pref is 5x the touch-start tolerance pref. This\nseems to provide a reasonable behaviour for me, although this value could\nprobably be tuned.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 63aAyGCbvoN", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/AsyncPanZoomController.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/AsyncPanZoomController.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/GestureEventListener.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/GestureEventListener.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxPrefs.h", "mobile/android/app/mobile.js", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa9cdc61ccc222bf0bc852a9d999e561ccb5e441", "parents": ["8b4fbaa0a0de8752ec212789f465eb62ca17f3b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392322 - Fix browserAction.setTitle for currently active tab on Android. r=mixedpuppy, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1Wka0zFxElD", "files": ["mobile/android/components/extensions/ext-browserAction.js", "mobile/android/components/extensions/test/mochitest/test_ext_browserAction_getTitle_setTitle.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9e2fda5c1b955de6c341a3d41c30751eee5fd833", "parents": ["fa9cdc61ccc222bf0bc852a9d999e561ccb5e441"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1347518 - Part 1: Use SEI recovery point to mark keyframe. r=jesup, a=lizzard\n\nSome streams do not include any IDR frames. However, they do include SEI recovery point markers. We use those to mark keyframes.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IHfUx7fEgEJ", "files": ["media/libstagefright/binding/H264.cpp", "media/libstagefright/binding/include/mp4_demuxer/H264.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb8967e983b19fe45dafda52e81809d938ca93ca", "parents": ["9e2fda5c1b955de6c341a3d41c30751eee5fd833"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1347518 - Part 2: Don't attempt to determine frame type when encrypted. r=cpearce, a=lizzard\n\nThe data being encrypted, is nonsensical. So we always rely on the container information\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4uQ9l3Q1Ebl", "files": ["dom/media/fmp4/MP4Demuxer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e070c1cca1be6f9c51f70ea9ac6f557c6dd76e8f", "parents": ["fb8967e983b19fe45dafda52e81809d938ca93ca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Froman \u003cmfroman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391857 - Fix ctx flags for e10s stun addr gathering. r=drno, a=lizzard\n\nIn the case of e10s, the ctx flags for default route only (and less\nimportantly in this case, proxy only) were not set on the ice ctx\nwhen SetStunAddrs was called in PeerConnectionMedia.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CldUpJfaaH3", "files": ["media/mtransport/nricectx.cpp", "media/mtransport/nricectx.h", "media/mtransport/third_party/nICEr/src/ice/ice_ctx.c", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/PeerConnectionMedia.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b20ed3e703900cc9a64ebd17bb026a55a1e3f4ac", "parents": ["e070c1cca1be6f9c51f70ea9ac6f557c6dd76e8f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391628 - Use fallback locale on nsICollation if locale is invalid. r=emk, a=lizzard\n\nOriginal issue is that Microsoft Dynamics CRM uses invalid lang attribute in \u003cxsl:sort\u003e.\n\n\u003cxsl:sort order=\"descending\"\n          select=\"@displayname[$sortColumnName='displayname'] |\n                  @name[$sortColumnName='name'] |\n                  exslt:node-set($FriendlyTypeNames)/types/type[@xmlName=current()/@datatype and $sortColumnName='datatype']\"\n          lang=\"$languageName\"/\u003e\n\nOur XSLT implementation detects \"$languageName\" as locale name, then use it to nsICollation.\n\nUntil Gecko 54 for Windows, even if using invalid locale name for nsICollation, it uses platform locale as fallback.  But from 55, we use same implementation as macOS's to use ICU.  So this issue occurs.  ICU implementation doesn't use fallback locale if it is invalid.\n\nWe should use fallback locale if locale is invalid.  Most code for fallback locale such as FallbackEncoding uses application locale, so use it.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EKYkZG7Hnz0", "files": ["intl/locale/nsCollation.cpp", "intl/locale/tests/gtest/TestCollation.cpp", "intl/locale/tests/gtest/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e08568b12c294e87a2b0035cee4d9d174ccac0e8", "parents": ["b20ed3e703900cc9a64ebd17bb026a55a1e3f4ac"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391645 - Make nsPrintEngine::SetupToPrintContent() proceed with the print even when mPrt-\u003emPrintObject-\u003emPresShell and mPrt-\u003emPrintObject-\u003emPresContext are nullptr but mIsCreatingPrintPreview is false. r=dholbert, a=lizzard\n\nBug 1376693 added a null-check to bail from print operations if\nmPresShell/mPresContext are null, to avoid some null-deref crashes.  However,\nit turns out it's possible for these variables to be null under normal\nconditions -- for example, when nsPrintEngine is printing documents,\nmPrt-\u003emPrintObject-\u003emPresShell and mPrt-\u003emPrintObject-\u003emPresShell can be nullptr\nif the document has \u003cframeset\u003e element and it's printing only content of a\n\u003cframe\u003e element or all \u003cframe\u003e elements separately.\n\nThis special frameset-printing mode can cause these variables to be null;\nhowever, the crash occurred only when mIsCreatingPrintPreview is true.  So,\nwe should check the variables only when it's true.\n\nFortunately:\n    * the null-deref crashes that Bug 1376693 wanted to avoid were all in code\n      that we only visit when mIsCreatingPrintPreview is true (i.e. during print\n      preview).\n    * this special frameset-printing mode (which causes these variables to be\n      null) _cannot be used during print preview_.\n\nSo, we can avoid the print-preview-specific crashes without breaking\nframeset-printing by simply making our null-check bail-out conditional on\nmIsCreatingPrintPreview.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FJ3ynrXTxnI", "files": ["layout/printing/nsPrintEngine.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b185b492e4eedf396ce4ca68bbfce04523025046", "parents": ["e08568b12c294e87a2b0035cee4d9d174ccac0e8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Boris Zbarsky \u003cbzbarsky@mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393063 - Part 1: Fix IPCStreamSource's handling of async streams returning 0 from Available. r=bkelly, a=lizzard\n\nThis aligns the code more closely with how the input stream pump works: 0\navailable bytes when the stream itself told us it's ready means the stream is at\nthe end.\n\nNote from asuth: This fix was originally part of bug 1371699, it was part 5.\nHowever, its initial landing was backed out, but it is now very much needed for\nbug 1393063, so I'm landing it.", "files": ["ipc/glue/IPCStreamSource.cpp", "ipc/glue/IPCStreamSource.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6a38cf9003c60bc5158627e2048b6a4f2dab8683", "parents": ["b185b492e4eedf396ce4ca68bbfce04523025046"], "tags": []}, {"author": "steveck-chung \u003cschung@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390816 - Part 1: Add addresses sync checkbox in first time saving doorhanger. r=lchang, a=lizzard, l10n=flod\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KkpseMw4kRk", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillDoorhanger.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/locales/en-US/formautofill.properties"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "02852b5a5b3c6b13029da12b9da5060f88ee2222", "parents": ["6a38cf9003c60bc5158627e2048b6a4f2dab8683"], "tags": []}], "date": 1503944721, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7687": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mantaroh Yoshinaga \u003cmantaroh@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1366603 - Wait for rAF before waiting the MozAfterPaint in test_deferred_start.html. r=hiro, a=test-only\n\nThis test called waitForPaints() after creating an animation, but waitForPaints()\ndidn't wait for a MozAfterPaint event actually since\nDOMWindowUtils.IsMozAfterPaintPending which is checked a MozAfterPaint event has\nbeen queued return false[1]. (i.e. This test didn't wait for a MozAfterPaint)\n\nThis is related to bug 1341294. If gecko can receive a MozAfterPaint\ncorresponded to own paint, waitForPaint() does not need to check for\nDOMWindowUtils.IsMozAfterPaintPending.\n\nThis patch is a workaround until bug 1341294 is resolved.\n\n[1] http://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/5696c3e525fc8222674eed6a562f5fcbe804c4c7/testing/mochitest/tests/SimpleTest/paint_listener.js#60\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6Rnv8MBP6Se", "files": ["dom/animation/test/mozilla/file_deferred_start.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bc8f7e510cc8955cf6041dc4e0577622f3e1b382", "parents": ["02852b5a5b3c6b13029da12b9da5060f88ee2222"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390346 - Redirects to moz-extension:-URLs fail when loaded from a xpi. r=jimm, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2FzUWLTiLs", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js", "netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e9c83e49ec46b763d0529edcb9580837739ba639", "parents": ["bc8f7e510cc8955cf6041dc4e0577622f3e1b382"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390346 - Test jar caching in combination with redirects. r=rpl, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6sFdcruieh6", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/mochitest/mochitest-common.ini", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/mochitest/test_ext_redirect_jar.html", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_i18n_css.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2968e01b6f206a949ea8f941a3f86b6738828114", "parents": ["e9c83e49ec46b763d0529edcb9580837739ba639"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393402 - Set longer timeout for document load. r=mixedpuppy, a=test-only on a CLOSED TREE\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BSWPMaNvtwG", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/mochitest/test_ext_redirect_jar.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8081a895e4353e807a851485e412ed7a907c0b3f", "parents": ["2968e01b6f206a949ea8f941a3f86b6738828114"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_56_0b7_RELEASE", "FENNEC_56_0b7_BUILD1", "FENNEC_56_0b7_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_56_0b7_BUILD2", "FIREFOX_56_0b7_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1503946435, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7688": {"changesets": [{"author": "sotaro \u003csotaro.ikeda.g@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387659 - Add Layer::Disconnect() calling in LayerTransactionParent::Destroy(). r=nical, a=abillings", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/LayerTransactionParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f5944141d7779944001a570cd7a49818e7463966", "parents": ["8081a895e4353e807a851485e412ed7a907c0b3f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391218 - Fix 'getDocShellEnumerator is not a function' exception when closing the last tab in a window. r=ochameau, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FUcCCljVClI", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/chrome.js", "devtools/server/actors/tab.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e8f74618acb2729323e34b8d0c0aa4b12a7cd530", "parents": ["f5944141d7779944001a570cd7a49818e7463966"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392872 - Fix missing startup/shutdown reason in LegacyExtensionsUtils. r=aswan, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: K8pyxR7Vhpl", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/LegacyExtensionsUtils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "04a9ce3155dcdd26e2a24007d3b61ee2bc5f746e", "parents": ["e8f74618acb2729323e34b8d0c0aa4b12a7cd530"], "tags": []}, {"author": "gasolin \u003cgasolin@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388813 - [Onboarding] Expand Tour Notification description width to allow longer descrition. r=rexboy, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JykTLLGed8m", "files": ["browser/extensions/onboarding/content/onboarding.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4ea3381ed58194eeaa98fce8fec560b83ba8a679", "parents": ["04a9ce3155dcdd26e2a24007d3b61ee2bc5f746e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504010331, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7689": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nde -\u003e 3dc912dd78ac\neo -\u003e 8269fd9a836e\nms -\u003e 00203e5aa8b3\npl -\u003e 2e3d940fc465", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c21f66c8d36d8c5dccdac518ddf89a1e442d7817", "parents": ["4ea3381ed58194eeaa98fce8fec560b83ba8a679"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504011627, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7690": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\neo -\u003e e67e5f4e4e07", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5ef3deb43f7d523b975e48c268ddf46d18191345", "parents": ["c21f66c8d36d8c5dccdac518ddf89a1e442d7817"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504018822, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7691": {"changesets": [{"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1378577 - Fix await race condition which causes intermittent timeouts in test_stylesheet_clone_import_rule.html. r=emilio, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2vWsCcnsmwF", "files": ["layout/style/test/chrome/test_stylesheet_clone_import_rule.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f105366cc45d84bfe9d41a1c411d2f6b8fc47cdc", "parents": ["5ef3deb43f7d523b975e48c268ddf46d18191345"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Mielczarek \u003cted@mielczarek.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1371992 - Make mozlint's LintRoller use concurrent.futures. r=ahal, a=test-only\n\nThere's a persistent test failure in automation that seems to have to do\nwith shutting down the `multiprocessing.Manager` that's used to get a\n`Queue` to submit jobs to worker processes. After toying around with fixing\nthat I decided it would be simpler to just use concurrent.futures here,\nsince we already have it in-tree and it fits the use case here better\nthan using raw multiprocessing.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8DdSvs2qp0q", "files": ["python/mozlint/mozlint/roller.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6664fab5dea98a05b834b75583dd9029c279dab9", "parents": ["f105366cc45d84bfe9d41a1c411d2f6b8fc47cdc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Joel Maher \u003cjmaher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393583 - Reduce chunks of reftest on osx; remove reftest-stylo for osx. r=jryans, a=test-only", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/test/tests.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dac913e90cba86c934d5302814c823a3e7c34caf", "parents": ["6664fab5dea98a05b834b75583dd9029c279dab9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388590 - StreamingLexer::Clone should bail if SourceBufferIterator::Advance returns not ready. r=tnikkel, a=lizzard\n\nStreamingLexer::Clone should always succeed because we are merely\ncreating a new SourceBufferIterator which is at the same position as the\ngiven iterator. However it is possible if there is no more data after,\nthe current position, it could return COMPLETE instead of READY.\n\nThis should not happen during the first Advance loop however. We handle\nthe failure gracefully now, and if someone files a report with the\ninvalid ICO file causing this problem, then we can investigate further.", "files": ["image/StreamingLexer.h", "image/decoders/nsICODecoder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "45080fa9b68c260a3f493e3415993a82c4eff826", "parents": ["dac913e90cba86c934d5302814c823a3e7c34caf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1382260 - Part 1: Fix file access test bug. r=Alex_Gaynor, a=lizzard\n\nFix the file access check by adding missing parentheses to isDirectory method call.\n\nDon't run the cookies file check on Linux because the test profile is read accessible due to being in /tmp.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: lps2hk8f5U", "files": ["security/sandbox/test/browser_content_sandbox_fs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a84600cca0fe71ad285cb8b87894c00cebe2ed48", "parents": ["45080fa9b68c260a3f493e3415993a82c4eff826"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1382260 - Part 2: [Mac] Allow reading of font files from the content sandbox. r=Alex_Gaynor, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9W5aqQweFmd", "files": ["security/sandbox/mac/SandboxPolicies.h", "security/sandbox/test/browser_content_sandbox_fs.js", "security/sandbox/test/browser_content_sandbox_utils.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "63df2314c2ddc556543b9423fc036c1819f24b7c", "parents": ["a84600cca0fe71ad285cb8b87894c00cebe2ed48"], "tags": []}, {"author": "JerryShih \u003chshih@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1379995 - Reset the mBufferFetchingIsVerified flag after the webgl deleteBuffer call. r=jgilbert, a=lizzard\n\nIf the buffer status was changed, we should do the ValidateBufferFetching() again.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7czQFT3qauE", "files": ["dom/canvas/WebGLContextBuffers.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ce34f6b654226fd096e6d720b00625ffc19678b2", "parents": ["63df2314c2ddc556543b9423fc036c1819f24b7c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "JerryShih \u003chshih@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1379995 - Test case for webgl drawArray() call. r=jgilbert, a=lizzard\n\nTest drawArray() after calling deleteBuffer() for the binded buffer.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 306tsklZK4L", "files": ["dom/canvas/test/webgl-mochitest/test_fuzzing_bugs.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "30438603946a724dc538051ee949e4d7c3fcfff1", "parents": ["ce34f6b654226fd096e6d720b00625ffc19678b2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1382335 - 4. Check for shutdown in more LayerViewSupport functions. r=esawin, a=lizzard\n\nCheck for shutdown so we don't crash on accessing a null window pointer.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FRky4dcuhrw", "files": ["widget/android/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a320ecb85b4708b551ee1480481e208e94dc2efc", "parents": ["30438603946a724dc538051ee949e4d7c3fcfff1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1382335 - 5. Check for shutdown in LayerViewSupport::OnResumedEvent. r=esawin, a=lizzard\n\nIt wasn't enough to just check for `mWindow` in `OnResumedCompositor()`,\nbecause the `LayerViewSupport` instance itself could have been released.\nThis patch now checks for both cases.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: hSnFUhtp8m", "files": ["widget/android/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5c47a18fc05faef9f12d3dd1f23b6e77444ad733", "parents": ["a320ecb85b4708b551ee1480481e208e94dc2efc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Forshaw \u003cforshaw@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1385928 - Take new implementation of GetProcessBaseAddress from chromium commit f398005bc4ca0cc2dab2198faa99d4ee8f4da60d. r=jimm, a=lizzard\n\nThis should fix issues we have seen with running Firefox from short name paths or moved binaries.", "files": ["security/sandbox/chromium/sandbox/win/src/nt_internals.h", "security/sandbox/chromium/sandbox/win/src/win_utils.cc", "security/sandbox/chromium/sandbox/win/src/win_utils.h", "security/sandbox/modifications-to-chromium-to-reapply-after-upstream-merge.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b6804ce9ce65c7f3156c16e229e74ba7d1c5802", "p