bb1978e8c7bd713f863ac7103cc1200c9311", "parents": ["6f0cfcff6de6c0f688ba7ccae8ff3e9ecc8d5abc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388611 - Update mProfileName after a profile reset to handle multiple consecutive resets. r=Dolske, a=sledru\n\nFollow-up to bug 1122124 to ensure `SaveWordToEnvIfUnset(\"XRE_PROFILE_NAME\", mProfileName);` saves the updated profile name after reset takes the old profiles name.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: MTJAQUKktM", "files": ["toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "977ac95baf61ee0121c7b3ade92b274e5cb391a0", "parents": ["5a73bb1978e8c7bd713f863ac7103cc1200c9311"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388611 - Preserve .sqlite-wal files with a Firefox Reset. r=mak, a=sledru\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: At6IY39uNPt", "files": ["browser/components/migration/FirefoxProfileMigrator.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e951f52ac4b62291789ff582a723705d15fa0406", "parents": ["977ac95baf61ee0121c7b3ade92b274e5cb391a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luke Wagner \u003cluke@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395100 - Don't pass around a mutable Iter*. r=jandem, a=abillings\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Syy4Qtt55F", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/ion/bug1395100.js", "js/src/jit/arm/Assembler-arm.cpp", "js/src/jit/arm/Assembler-arm.h", "js/src/shell/js.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e65e640970ef101defb3e75fb4186741157c8b11", "parents": ["e951f52ac4b62291789ff582a723705d15fa0406"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395598 - Correct LocalStorage mozStorage misuse. r=janv, a=abillings", "files": ["dom/storage/StorageDBThread.cpp", "dom/storage/StorageIPC.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4e46cd56c813f0f31ea234e345ee022c5ec7840b", "parents": ["e65e640970ef101defb3e75fb4186741157c8b11"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504365296, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7708": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\ndsb -\u003e 647387266640\nhy-AM -\u003e 5add0d31e3fe\nru -\u003e 3747c6476aa9\nth -\u003e 8373151042bb", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "da291ce74248b2830a0010a8bf21bba5f408bd43", "parents": ["4e46cd56c813f0f31ea234e345ee022c5ec7840b"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_56_0b9_RELEASE", "FENNEC_56_0b9_BUILD3", "FENNEC_56_0b9_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_56_0b9_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_56_0b9_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1504447223, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7709": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Prince", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b1_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1387524 - Back out removal of MOZ_PRETTY to build Thunderbird 56 beta\n\nBackout most of changeset 318f1bcd336e from bug 1329355 to support building releases on buildbot. a=jorgk\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: K4QAA8IIpVX", "files": ["toolkit/locales/l10n.mk", "toolkit/mozapps/installer/package-name.mk"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4d743cec7db7372c4b75561e603fd1c0fe4ba0e7", "parents": ["da291ce74248b2830a0010a8bf21bba5f408bd43"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b1_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1385905 - part2: HTMLEditRules::SplitParagraph() should insert normal \u003cbr\u003e element rather than moz-\u003cbr\u003e element if split element and/or new element is empty r=m_kato a=jorgk\n\nCurrently, HTMLEditRules::SplitParagraph() inserts moz-\u003cbr\u003e element when split element and/or new element causes empty line.  However, PlaintextSerializer ignores moz-\u003cbr\u003e elements.  Therefore, empty lines which are created by SplitParagraph() will be removed when it's converted to plaintext.\n\nSo, it should insert normal \u003cbr\u003e element for placeholder of empty lines instead.  Note that moz-\u003cbr\u003e elements are appeared as normal \u003cbr\u003e elements in the result of Element.innerHTML.  Additionally, Chromium always inserts a \u003cbr\u003e element for empty block elements which are created by Enter key press.  Therefore, using normal \u003cbr\u003e element in this case shouldn't cause any compatibility problems.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FNV41zEFWqQ", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.h", "editor/libeditor/TextEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/TextEditRules.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8c436ac0dd5b79fb6f16b6a4e2885dfa05203b9", "parents": ["4d743cec7db7372c4b75561e603fd1c0fe4ba0e7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b1_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1350152 - Don't rely on gBrowser in nsLoginManagerPrompter.js. r=mkaply a=jorgk\n\nIn bug 1266836 we fixed this code to properly work in e10s,\nbut made the mistake of using gBrowser in toolkit code, breaking\nXUL apps that don't have a gBrowser. This solution implements\na different code-path for non-e10s and returns a chrome\nwindow for consumers that don't offer a browser.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 929ahDenzu5", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/nsLoginManagerPrompter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b0cfae189ff0068b21a9908b0e35bc56f9b01704", "parents": ["a8c436ac0dd5b79fb6f16b6a4e2885dfa05203b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jorg K \u003cjorgk@jorgk.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b1_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1388166 - Handle case where chromeWin.getBrowser() doesn't exist. r=johannh a=jorgk DONTBUILD", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/nsLoginManagerPrompter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dda5b3b1e69dd5d2c5768bda73ff94d8e9ac7939", "parents": ["b0cfae189ff0068b21a9908b0e35bc56f9b01704"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504522632, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "mozilla@jorgk.com"}, "7710": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jorg K \u003cjorgk@jorgk.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b1_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Branch closed due to incorrect naming. a=jorgk DONTBUILD", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a425407decadbcf4c55f927ff3a8c2a98ed00a6", "parents": ["dda5b3b1e69dd5d2c5768bda73ff94d8e9ac7939"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504523144, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mozilla@jorgk.com"}, "7711": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Prince", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b4_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1387524 - Back out removal of MOZ_PRETTY to build Thunderbird 56 beta. a=jorgk\n\nBackout most of changeset 318f1bcd336e from bug 1329355 to support building releases on buildbot.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: K4QAA8IIpVX", "files": ["toolkit/locales/l10n.mk", "toolkit/mozapps/installer/package-name.mk"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8e9ecc194f1a573ca4414cd617e5c33aaa2b08c2", "parents": ["da291ce74248b2830a0010a8bf21bba5f408bd43"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b4_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1385905 - part2: HTMLEditRules::SplitParagraph() should insert normal \u003cbr\u003e element rather than moz-\u003cbr\u003e element if split element and/or new element is empty r=m_kato a=jorgk\n\nCurrently, HTMLEditRules::SplitParagraph() inserts moz-\u003cbr\u003e element when split element and/or new element causes empty line.  However, PlaintextSerializer ignores moz-\u003cbr\u003e elements.  Therefore, empty lines which are created by SplitParagraph() will be removed when it's converted to plaintext.\n\nSo, it should insert normal \u003cbr\u003e element for placeholder of empty lines instead.  Note that moz-\u003cbr\u003e elements are appeared as normal \u003cbr\u003e elements in the result of Element.innerHTML.  Additionally, Chromium always inserts a \u003cbr\u003e element for empty block elements which are created by Enter key press.  Therefore, using normal \u003cbr\u003e element in this case shouldn't cause any compatibility problems.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FNV41zEFWqQ", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.h", "editor/libeditor/TextEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/TextEditRules.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8b9bfd6bdb81a6454e6cb6e728b4deb3dd238c3", "parents": ["8e9ecc194f1a573ca4414cd617e5c33aaa2b08c2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b4_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1350152 - Don't rely on gBrowser in nsLoginManagerPrompter.js. r=mkaply a=jorgk\n\nIn bug 1266836 we fixed this code to properly work in e10s,\nbut made the mistake of using gBrowser in toolkit code, breaking\nXUL apps that don't have a gBrowser. This solution implements\na different code-path for non-e10s and returns a chrome\nwindow for consumers that don't offer a browser.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 929ahDenzu5", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/nsLoginManagerPrompter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4749211b02221a75ccaf1bc277f5dd52cf079017", "parents": ["a8b9bfd6bdb81a6454e6cb6e728b4deb3dd238c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jorg K \u003cjorgk@jorgk.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b4_2017090401_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1388166 - Handle case where chromeWin.getBrowser() doesn't exist. r=johannh a=jorgk DONTBUILD", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/nsLoginManagerPrompter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5acd7637b488eb221ea62b6c674adc992de41892", "parents": ["4749211b02221a75ccaf1bc277f5dd52cf079017"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504523481, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "mozilla@jorgk.com"}, "7712": {"changesets": [{"author": "Chih-Yi Leu \u003csubsevenx2001@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1319160 - Remove redundant webgl disjoint timer extension mochitest. r=jgilbert, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GCUNxcIiF8F", "files": ["dom/canvas/test/webgl-mochitest/mochitest.ini", "dom/canvas/test/webgl-mochitest/test_webgl_disjoint_timer_query.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ce3f57d9051d349bb4a31676c049a84a085c34d9", "parents": ["da291ce74248b2830a0010a8bf21bba5f408bd43"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394493 - Check for uninitialised lexicals in getModuleEnvironmentValue(). r=arai, a=test-only", "files": ["js/src/builtin/TestingFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jit-test/tests/modules/bug1394493.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "06408f33c66c31b39e9b3a45d7592b13d06bd18c", "parents": ["ce3f57d9051d349bb4a31676c049a84a085c34d9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daosheng Mu \u003cdaoshengmu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1386664 - Add Knuckles string id for SteamVR Knuckles controllers. r=kip, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: H8fX21j0u6F", "files": ["gfx/vr/gfxVROpenVR.cpp", "gfx/vr/gfxVROpenVR.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fbbcff950d93dfcdc1b1cf79778ad16b7d27d00f", "parents": ["06408f33c66c31b39e9b3a45d7592b13d06bd18c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Edouard Oger \u003ceoger@fastmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390586 - Center search icon in Synced Tabs sidebar on Windows. r=Gijs, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3ecUrJe0UPd", "files": ["browser/themes/linux/syncedtabs/sidebar.css", "browser/themes/windows/syncedtabs/sidebar.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "95c49dd1457cd63b284d84d6cb27e179fdf7cdd1", "parents": ["fbbcff950d93dfcdc1b1cf79778ad16b7d27d00f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brian Grinstead \u003cbgrinstead@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1389939 - Stop syncing devtools theme and compact themes. r=Gijs, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GUjgHU5pgg1", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/devtools-browser.js", "devtools/client/framework/test/browser_toolbox_theme.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a2bbac5af2999a741bd501e59543668451a43cad", "parents": ["95c49dd1457cd63b284d84d6cb27e179fdf7cdd1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Bolter \u003cdbolter@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391733 - Update telemetry to provide information about e10s incompatible jaws usage. r=surkov, a=gchang", "files": ["accessible/windows/ia2/ia2Accessible.cpp", "accessible/windows/msaa/Compatibility.cpp", "accessible/windows/msaa/Compatibility.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a10406f37137c079fca3676705bc26614a3279a0", "parents": ["a2bbac5af2999a741bd501e59543668451a43cad"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luke Chang \u003clchang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393083 - [Form Autofill] CJK names should be combined in the order: familyName + givenName. r=steveck, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DnRKx60dsUX", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillNameUtils.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_transformFields.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6103dced6357550c32f01fee5a5605b9fe9f5eee", "parents": ["a10406f37137c079fca3676705bc26614a3279a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gian-Carlo Pascutto \u003cgcp@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391494 - Enforce use of our own copy of strlcpy. r=jld, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GQgGJBj1Hjc", "files": ["security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBrokerRealpath.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e2beb66c58e022fa22d7aa94566933ab74549bcb", "parents": ["6103dced6357550c32f01fee5a5605b9fe9f5eee"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393624 - Blacklist more invalid characters found in Apple's fonts. r=jrmuizel, a=gchang", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxMacPlatformFontList.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fe4bfcfc5db2aeee3d90a759ea224a12c405778e", "parents": ["e2beb66c58e022fa22d7aa94566933ab74549bcb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392755 - Use a normal thread instead of LazyIdleThread for QuotaManager IO thread. r=jvarga, a=gchang\n\nQuotaManager is now a hip, popular subsystem used by many consumers, many of\nwhich are now latency sensitive.  There is no longer any meaningful benefit to\nusing LazyIdleThread, but there are latency downsides.  Also, LazyIdleThread\nhas some bugs at shutdown and complications for callers that use\nNS_GetCurrentThread().  So, begone LazyIdleThread!", "files": ["dom/quota/ActorsParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cdd1559ed4d3e99e5e01941aa4cce99be2518138", "parents": ["fe4bfcfc5db2aeee3d90a759ea224a12c405778e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504530987, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7713": {"changesets": [{"author": "tbirdbld", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b4_2017090411_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Automated checkin: version bump for thunderbird 56.0b4 release. DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE a=release", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "53e74017d772dab5aa4eb5e5c1dddb83b9697db5", "parents": ["5acd7637b488eb221ea62b6c674adc992de41892"], "tags": ["THUNDERBIRD_56_0b4_BUILD1"]}, {"author": "tbirdbld", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD560b4_2017090411_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Added THUNDERBIRD_56_0b4_RELEASE THUNDERBIRD_56_0b4_BUILD1 tag(s) for changeset 53e74017d772. DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE a=release", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "12b0a2c4f950f512adc2216520990a8438a4115c", "parents": ["53e74017d772dab5aa4eb5e5c1dddb83b9697db5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504539040, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "tbirdbld"}, "7714": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nick Thomas \u003cnthomas@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387622 - add latest-ssl aliases for bedrock, r=mtabara, a=release\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8s1CiEdL6cG", "files": ["testing/mozharness/configs/releases/bouncer_firefox_beta.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/releases/bouncer_firefox_esr.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/releases/bouncer_firefox_release.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "837b0dc3e6ee86e60f00111d244146d708d012a5", "parents": ["cdd1559ed4d3e99e5e01941aa4cce99be2518138"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504567261, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "nthomas@mozilla.com"}, "7715": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nde -\u003e a475d339a8a8\net -\u003e f94a081742e2\nhi-IN -\u003e fc356e571b70\nkk -\u003e bf9944b60c94\nms -\u003e 914ba4c10c9b\nuk -\u003e a81c48ed4ecd", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f35c0df3ab8e7091d45bea7b653bbcb4d8dc40e", "parents": ["837b0dc3e6ee86e60f00111d244146d708d012a5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504598424, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7716": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump. CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5c6a0d51f4bbb51c37321f44c1752d6cd96d271e", "parents": ["0f35c0df3ab8e7091d45bea7b653bbcb4d8dc40e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging da291ce74248b2830a0010a8bf21bba5f408bd43 with FENNEC_56_0b9_BUILD3, FENNEC_56_0b9_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "72a20e86b67a02fe180bf32f5526998e9fd52d55", "parents": ["5c6a0d51f4bbb51c37321f44c1752d6cd96d271e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504628139, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7717": {"changesets": [{"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1317900 - Address intermittent failure in test_ext_unload_frame.html. r=aswan, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8ySNL64KLmO", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/mochitest/test_ext_unload_frame.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6dd7c570d4807f6b279e859c90dc033f68b1e2fd", "parents": ["72a20e86b67a02fe180bf32f5526998e9fd52d55"], "tags": []}, {"author": "JW Wang \u003cjwwang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1348634 - Wait for the 'suspend' event to ensure resource cloning work as expected. r=cpearce, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BeGGnUfFDcN", "files": ["dom/media/test/test_load_same_resource.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1a0a1ec5c58f6c6aee9b4692810f314fe26b9cfb", "parents": ["6dd7c570d4807f6b279e859c90dc033f68b1e2fd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1363896 - Adjust fuzzy-if for Android's reftest. r=masayuki, a=test-only\n\neditor/reftests/input-text-onfocus-reframe-ref.html is sometimes failed due to \"image comparison, max difference: 1, number of differing pixels: 1\".\n\nAs long as I check both images, I don't know why focus ring is different.  But this is 1 pixel only diff, so we should use fuzz-if.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5SrjorXEBW", "files": ["editor/reftests/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8bdd1bbd948f52e7b5f3ab2c1168fece0ee14377", "parents": ["1a0a1ec5c58f6c6aee9b4692810f314fe26b9cfb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393402 - Fix intermittent by removing early testing timeout. r=mixedpuppy, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AAnS9cXlTz0", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/mochitest/test_ext_redirect_jar.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "569cb400470af584fd505e82a005e7c411b0422f", "parents": ["8bdd1bbd948f52e7b5f3ab2c1168fece0ee14377"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1373444 - Ignore exceptions during wpt test teardown. r=maja_zf, a=test-only\n\nIn general these exceptions are the result of something unexpected in\nthe environment, but shouldn't themseslves cause the test to error.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5XjJoT4UwnC", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/executors/executormarionette.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ba89ef7040e03c1c6e92a4adeeac0903124d6c80", "parents": ["569cb400470af584fd505e82a005e7c411b0422f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1373444 - Look for NoSuchWindowException when waiting for manual browser close in wpt. r=maja_zf, a=test-only\n\nThis method works by running a long-running script and catching the exception when\nit is interrupted. But the exception changed so we must make a corresponding change here.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EdZZAOVZ0Sw", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/executors/executormarionette.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d0fb17cf639bff43bde763ae81515bca8089047d", "parents": ["ba89ef7040e03c1c6e92a4adeeac0903124d6c80"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1366217 - Discard GC stats if timing inconsistencies are found. r=sfink, a=lizzard", "files": ["js/src/gc/Statistics.cpp", "js/src/vm/HelperThreads.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "83a250a0a345c83cac9a46c27f7a8c9dd77e264a", "parents": ["d0fb17cf639bff43bde763ae81515bca8089047d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387059 - When checking if nsDisplayPerspective participates in preserve-3d, check the underlying transformed frame. r=mstange, a=gchang", "files": ["dom/tests/mochitest/general/mochitest.ini", "dom/tests/mochitest/general/test_pointerPreserves3DPerspective.html", "layout/generic/nsIFrame.h", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c141e8fe733b1841f9fb1233eda37e01d9e88cb7", "parents": ["83a250a0a345c83cac9a46c27f7a8c9dd77e264a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kelly \u003cmkelly@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392960 - Do not hide \u003cpreferences\u003e elements for subcategories. r=jaws, a=gchang\n\nWhen filtering for which elements to hide when the user is viewing a\nsubcategory, \u003cpreferences\u003e elements are excluded (though they must still match\nthe category search).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EvSXgrhuJXl", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/preferences.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/tests/browser_bug1020245_openPreferences_to_paneContent.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f2654ea508ece686ba9503438d8729cadc0ec45b", "parents": ["c141e8fe733b1841f9fb1233eda37e01d9e88cb7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394661 - Use user locale instead of system locale for font fallback. r=gandalf, a=lizzard\n\nUntil Firefox 54, font fallback uses user locale.  Example, OS is Windows 10 JA with JA UI, Firefox uses JA font for fallback even if Firefox is US version.\n\nBut since we changed some locale code on Firefox 55 development cycle, there were some regressions such as bug 1346674.  So we changed fallback locale to system locale (instead of Firefox UX locale) for font selection by bug 1348259.\n\nIt isn't good for old compatibility, so we should use user locale for font fallback like Firefox 54.  Now we can get user locale by OSPreferences::GetRegionalPrefsLocales, use it for font fallback\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7qwDDeU1ZPt", "files": ["intl/locale/nsLanguageAtomService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9e3812ad55629e4532fa3ab8dfcee44ba2a91745", "parents": ["f2654ea508ece686ba9503438d8729cadc0ec45b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328008 - Stop collapsing TreeView nodes when clicking a value. r=Honza, a=gchang", "files": ["devtools/client/jsonview/test/browser_jsonview_valid_json.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/tree/tree-view.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a908673c1485e95e9d88cdf92d37b57ee859c1ed", "parents": ["9e3812ad55629e4532fa3ab8dfcee44ba2a91745"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335029 - Take into account SystemClockDrivers in fallback mode when dealing with AudioContext promises. r=jesup, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HBS6XGXDGf1", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e1a13a255fcf316653d2ab0e48505b389642dcaf", "parents": ["a908673c1485e95e9d88cdf92d37b57ee859c1ed"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luke Chang \u003clchang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387988 - [Form Autofill] Optimize \"findLabelElements\" function. r=MattN, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EGtBzv2GZFj", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillHeuristics.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_findLabelElements.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_getInfo.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "201e7d5bef2937e9c7e6e50bb69458a62ac07da9", "parents": ["e1a13a255fcf316653d2ab0e48505b389642dcaf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luke Chang \u003clchang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392888 - [Form Autofill] Avoid using getElementsByTagName. r=MattN, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7Km6xkR4ffq", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillHeuristics.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d1940f3854236047ea6c6be07280caa312ecb41b", "parents": ["201e7d5bef2937e9c7e6e50bb69458a62ac07da9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Owen \u003cbobowencode@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392570 - On Windows 7 don't attempt to use a job object for the sandbox when it will fail. r=jimm, data-r=rweiss, a=gchang\n\nThis patch also adds telemetry for when this occurs, breaking it down for local and remote sessions.", "files": ["security/sandbox/win/src/sandboxbroker/sandboxBroker.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "984bda56d03cebb368dd9340fa892bdd41b0b5d0", "parents": ["d1940f3854236047ea6c6be07280caa312ecb41b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395289 - Convert from points to pixels when invalidating rect for screensharing when building on OS X older than 10.8. r=jesup, a=lizzard\n\nWhen we build for versions of OS X below 10.8 it is still necessary to\nconvert from points to pixels when invalidating rectangles as we use the\nCGRegisterScreenRefreshCallback and CGRegisterMoveCallback interfaces.", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/desktop_capture/screen_capturer_mac.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "edd07c36dc0dc87e587fbfc61aec8916d4226661", "parents": ["984bda56d03cebb368dd9340fa892bdd41b0b5d0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Hammond \u003cmhammond@skippinet.com.au\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391488 - Catch and ignore errors fetching the hostname from the DNS service. r=kitcambridge, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5hTDNmzTXdQ", "files": ["services/sync/modules/util.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1982424e5bea530697bbc0f468be8bf6f71072a1", "parents": ["edd07c36dc0dc87e587fbfc61aec8916d4226661"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396361 - Avoid crashing when some system library calls malloc_zone_free(zone, NULL). r=njn, a=gchang\n\nSome system libraries call malloc_zone_free directly instead of free,\nand sometimes they do that with the wrong zone. When that happens, we\ncircle back, trying to find the right zone, and call malloc_zone_free\nwith the right one, but when we can't find one, we crash, which matches\nwhat the system free() would do. Except in one case where the pointer\nwe're being passed is NULL, in which case we can't trace it back to any\nzone, but shouldn't crash (system free() explicitly doesn't crash in\nthat case).", "files": ["memory/build/zone.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e0216397b51aea53aceb9da50dadadc0b2ffacbb", "parents": ["1982424e5bea530697bbc0f468be8bf6f71072a1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504651257, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7718": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging da291ce74248b2830a0010a8bf21bba5f408bd43 with FIREFOX_56_0b9_BUILD1, FIREFOX_56_0b9_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "108e27d269372f7c0acb0cf02a499df8791ea4ba", "parents": ["e0216397b51aea53aceb9da50dadadc0b2ffacbb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504679766, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7719": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e 2963daf74d7b\nast -\u003e 600b5c347dd6\nbn-BD -\u003e 6887e9e44b4f\ncy -\u003e c9b7bbe88a11\neo -\u003e ee9b9751dcc2\nis -\u003e faf1bbd32dcd\nsl -\u003e 46e81e9e1539\ntr -\u003e 7160ba0717ce", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1e59f49ef429c07bd24cbca2179540ea5cffe705", "parents": ["108e27d269372f7c0acb0cf02a499df8791ea4ba"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504710025, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7720": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nfa -\u003e ccbc4db59445\nta -\u003e 01c1bbb7cdc8", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "97bee4069ef3dc6dba83760a80293c9a17b803f4", "parents": ["1e59f49ef429c07bd24cbca2179540ea5cffe705"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504713634, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7721": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394377 - Increase default shutdown timeout to 120s. r=maja_zf, a=test-only\n\nThe background thread hang monitor will crash Firefox after 60s if\na shutdown is too slow. Debug builds are slower and as such Marionette\nwould force kill Firefox right before the hang monitor can kick in.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GGQFPEZ37dg", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d704dede3a8dd9f69d14931dec0479a5e8dbfc6f", "parents": ["97bee4069ef3dc6dba83760a80293c9a17b803f4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Geoff Brown \u003cgbrown@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1373945 - Skip test_beaconPreflightWithCustomContentType.html on Android, for intermittent failures. a=test-only", "files": ["dom/tests/mochitest/beacon/mochitest.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "21853166224870ad8930d3742ef801812aa3f7b6", "parents": ["d704dede3a8dd9f69d14931dec0479a5e8dbfc6f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julien Cristau \u003cjcristau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388155 - Bump security preload information expiration dates to 2018-01-16 for Firefox 56. r=keeler, a=lizzard", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a3debc85f08678400e250acea5afcdff51708ea", "parents": ["21853166224870ad8930d3742ef801812aa3f7b6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yury Delendik \u003cydelendik@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396914 - Fixes the ability to print large PDF documents. r=bdahl, a=lizzard", "files": ["browser/extensions/pdfjs/content/web/viewer.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a09fc917c9b91fd42602f9589896c40f0267dfb5", "parents": ["4a3debc85f08678400e250acea5afcdff51708ea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Silverberg \u003cbsilverberg@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1374552 - Fix i18n.getUILanguage so it does not replace dashes with underscores. r=mixedpuppy, a=gchang\n\nWhen we implemented this API we converted dashes in the language code to underscores because that is what Chrome did.\nChrome no longer does this, so we need to remove the code that does the replacing.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DuOQ218zXby", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionCommon.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_i18n.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_i18n_css.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cb905f9be690fd0dc9017a32951416eb85277c1e", "parents": ["a09fc917c9b91fd42602f9589896c40f0267dfb5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Nguyen \u003ctnguyen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394335 - Add correct unwanted list when users enable uncommon and unwanted software from preference page. r=francois, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Ju0M47AWGVA", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/privacy.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/tests/browser_security-2.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/security.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_security.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "90926a141c6dad8fa2041c7410f26ca0a1c88a25", "parents": ["cb905f9be690fd0dc9017a32951416eb85277c1e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393467 - Clip FreeType glyph bitmap to mask in Skia. r=jrmuizel, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9NqLj9SkHFo", "files": ["gfx/skia/skia/src/ports/SkFontHost_FreeType_common.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6f8e3d7b5e5a95d6b0a82ba54f8815b060e46913", "parents": ["90926a141c6dad8fa2041c7410f26ca0a1c88a25"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Layzell \u003cmichael@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1378281 - Take 2: Also check if the child is destroyed during ProvideWindowCommon. r=catalinb, a=gchang", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "73592705a693a4256e14f2e638e88d6fd514b869", "parents": ["6f8e3d7b5e5a95d6b0a82ba54f8815b060e46913"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dylan Roeh \u003cdroeh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390261 - Add external storage to permissions required in FilePicker.getPermissionsForMimeType. r=snorp, a=gchang", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/FilePicker.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b2becf0295ba7f42c9241aed598165d94dd1582", "parents": ["73592705a693a4256e14f2e638e88d6fd514b869"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Blake Kaplan \u003cmrbkap@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1368343 - Be paranoid about null TabChild. r=billm, a=gchang\n\nI had a theory about what was happening (that we're somehow closing the window\nbetween the attempt to open the channel and the resulting OnStartRequest), but\nwhen I attempted to test that I couldn't make it crash (in fact, closing the\nwindow calls Cancel on the stream and stops the OnStartRequest from\nhappening). So, I don't know what's causing this, but clearly we're failing to\nget a TabChild out, so let's stop crashing for the time being.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LeGJCvh26dm", "files": ["uriloader/exthandler/ExternalHelperAppChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d72533fac3a844b075009ee4a5aab5720b3224f2", "parents": ["3b2becf0295ba7f42c9241aed598165d94dd1582"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504725313, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7722": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1384127 - Skip browser_printpreview.js on Windows for frequent failures. a=test-only", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/general/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a000b6bed029de20f39d13d611dc5bff5d301eb0", "parents": ["d72533fac3a844b075009ee4a5aab5720b3224f2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dylan Roeh \u003cdroeh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391181 - Reimplement the quaternion to Tait-Bryan conversion for device orientation events. r=snorp, a=lizzard", "files": ["dom/system/nsDeviceSensors.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "42c4fe4f6b401316bee506a18eb7e9a11ac7532e", "parents": ["a000b6bed029de20f39d13d611dc5bff5d301eb0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1383905 - Push notifications should only use \"web\" content processes. r=bkelly, a=gchang\n\nThis introduces filtering to avoid attempting to dispatch notifications\nto WebExtensions processes and other types of content processes.\n\nThis is dependent upon bug 1395827 changing xpcshell to create its child\nprocesses with a remote type of \"web\" in order to not break the push\nxpcshell tests.", "files": ["dom/push/PushNotifier.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c6754e857100d864d472913efad3fae1f62f5da5", "parents": ["42c4fe4f6b401316bee506a18eb7e9a11ac7532e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395827 - Eliminate NO_REMOTE_TYPE and default GetNewOrUsedBrowserProcess() remote type arg. r=billm, a=gchang\n\nNO_REMOTE_TYPE seems to have been an artifact of introducing remote types and\nnot wanting to change things.  This eliminates the type, changing\nGetNewOrUsedBrowserProcess() to no longer use a default argument so that\ncallers must think about the remote type they want.  Additionally, the existing\ncall-site used by xpcshell in nsEmbedFunctions.cpp is updated to use the\nDEFAULT_REMOTE_TYPE of \"web\", as-is the unused nsAppRunner.cpp case.  (That is,\nno one appears to call nsXULAppInfo::EnsureContentProcess directly or via its\nXPCOM interface, and so it probably should be removed.  However, since I\npotentially want this patch uplifted to beta 56 and legacy extensions exist\nthere, we're not addressing that in this patch.)", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentParent.h", "toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.cpp", "toolkit/xre/nsEmbedFunctions.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6c0e0e20b8e04ede4645d8553d655b3543cc944b", "parents": ["c6754e857100d864d472913efad3fae1f62f5da5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ray Lin \u003cralin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395173 - Part 1: Cache computed values in form handler instance instead of prototype. r=lchang, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Dwz6EmJ4VmN", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillHandler.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a758d80438a4a37f01c198fdd832e35d2cec8dbc", "parents": ["6c0e0e20b8e04ede4645d8553d655b3543cc944b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ray Lin \u003cralin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395173 - Part 2: Add a mochitest for the display of form autofill popup while switching between forms. r=lchang, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2DZr91ZR2zF", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/test/mochitest/formautofill_common.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/mochitest/mochitest.ini", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/mochitest/test_multiple_forms.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9055f0524b2de6d2b076ca2068e59fcecb85cd1b", "parents": ["a758d80438a4a37f01c198fdd832e35d2cec8dbc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336772 - Request any restyles required by changes to the cascade result. r=birtles, a=lizzard\n\nWhen an animation is newly created while the same property transition is\nrunning, the transition style rule persists until we call RequestRestyle() for\ntransitions level. That means if user calls getComputedStyle for the property\nright after creating animation, the style obtained by getComputedStyle still\nincluded the transitions level rule. As a result, the transitions level style\noverrides newly created animation style until the next normal restyling process\nhappens (i.e. process transition level restyle request). Vice versa, in the\ncase where an animation is removed, transitions level style does not appear\nuntil the next normal restyling.\n\nThis patch fixes this problem by trigerring a resyle of the transitions level\nwhen an animation is created or removed.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HY6amLmDHTi", "files": ["dom/animation/EffectCompositor.cpp", "dom/animation/EffectCompositor.h", "dom/animation/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/animation/test/mozilla/test_cascade.html", "layout/style/nsCSSPropertyIDSet.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4f6fcd8f33c7df235b23a94f7599accf11fd3950", "parents": ["9055f0524b2de6d2b076ca2068e59fcecb85cd1b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396292 - Part 1: Provide facilities to explicitly run permissions check callbacks on the background thread. r=sebastian, a=lizzard\n\nThe permissions check itself is synchronous, but if we then decide to prompt the user to acquire the permission, we have to do so asynchronously and eventually continue execution on the UI thread as a result. Therefore we need to provide a counterpart of onUIThread() for operations that want their callback to stay off the UI thread in all situations.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AOCX1v69R1J", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/permissions/PermissionBlock.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/permissions/Permissions.java", "mobile/android/tests/background/junit4/src/org/mozilla/gecko/permissions/TestPermissions.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "64b7ee7060ed09d4376dc7587001984f368e0b4d", "parents": ["4f6fcd8f33c7df235b23a94f7599accf11fd3950"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396292 - Part 2: Explicitly run permissions callback on background thread where applicable. r=sebastian, a=lizzard\n\nCurrently, this only concerns setImageAs, where not running on the UI thread after a permissions prompt triggers a network-related strict mode violation and interestingly enough results in a crash (as opposed to a logcat complaint) on release builds.\n\nThere's also a permissions check in the UpdateService which runs on a (but not *the*) background thread, but since we don't prompt in that case there's no action necessary.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KKxW96AyDWH", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoApp.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4bc7d657fca2ae674cebf2193a8d682a85918c05", "parents": ["64b7ee7060ed09d4376dc7587001984f368e0b4d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Francesco Lodolo (:flod) \u003cflod@lodolo.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396927 - Switch Diec2 (Catalan) search plugin to https. r=mkaply, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7JWJhqCvRJV", "files": ["browser/locales/searchplugins/diec2.xml", "mobile/locales/searchplugins/diec2.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "abc3387aaa6fcd05922670e0345f3b513285d8d7", "parents": ["4bc7d657fca2ae674cebf2193a8d682a85918c05"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504728763, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7723": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nfy-NL -\u003e 5442947be711\nms -\u003e 32dc3b2892c7\nro -\u003e 646687e76e79", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bfb0af0451ec5acf746f103e039c644f0efab641", "parents": ["abc3387aaa6fcd05922670e0345f3b513285d8d7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504774825, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7724": {"changesets": [{"author": "bechen@mozilla.com \u003cbechen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1372329 - Disable layout/reftests/webm-video/poster-2.html on Android 4.3. r=alwu, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CMzmIA8YI3i", "files": ["layout/reftests/webm-video/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8981f720907d11680ebd6c8e664e6600358fe108", "parents": ["bfb0af0451ec5acf746f103e039c644f0efab641"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Randall Barker \u003crbarker@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394526 - Ensure mouse events have the toolbar offset removed on Android. r=esawin, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DK8p9lOBVaS", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/gfx/NativePanZoomController.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "178da21590bb488edcc696d6131d6c399698d6be", "parents": ["8981f720907d11680ebd6c8e664e6600358fe108"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Parks \u003cdparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388903 - Part 1: Add PrintDlgW to x64 DLL Interceptor Test. r=jimm, a=gchang\n\nWe will hook PrintDlgW in another part.", "files": ["toolkit/xre/test/win/TestDllInterceptor.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9c1450703b0a43810727299bec81040573378912", "parents": ["178da21590bb488edcc696d6131d6c399698d6be"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Parks \u003cdparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388903 - Part 2: Remove PrintDlg Window Parentage in NPAPI Process. r=jimm, a=gchang\n\nBy intercepting the call to PrintDlgW and zeroing out the parent window privided by the caller, we allow the call to run in the NPAPI sandbox.", "files": ["dom/plugins/ipc/PluginModuleChild.cpp", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginQuirks.cpp", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginQuirks.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "755dff9960436d7feb9b9ee34e0d61f644ad9faa", "parents": ["9c1450703b0a43810727299bec81040573378912"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eric Rahm \u003cerahm@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393058 - Disable nsMemoryInfo dumper RT signal handling on Android. r=mccr8, a=lizzard\n\nIt appears some Android devices like to send spurious RT signals to our process\nwhich we interpret to mean a gc/cc log is being requested. This causes large\nfiles to pile up in the device storage. We can just disable this feature for\nAndroid as it would be pretty hard for a user to actually use (they can just\ngo to about:memory). Automation can still enable the FIFO queue if we ever\nwant to start dumping memory reports on device again.", "files": ["xpcom/base/nsMemoryInfoDumper.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7f6aade38935c08c783c23d51160427011f92ef2", "parents": ["755dff9960436d7feb9b9ee34e0d61f644ad9faa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392210 - Extension content needs nsIWebBrowserChrome3 for link traversal. r=kmag, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ITJhNL8FemG", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ext-browser-content.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7a6699a52aec8acfd69754f439b6fd0605d827c3", "parents": ["7f6aade38935c08c783c23d51160427011f92ef2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396302 - IMEStateManager::OnChangeFocusInternal() should check oldWidget's IME notification requests rather than sFocusedIMEWidget. r=m_kato, a=lizzard\n\nIn some cases, sFocusedIMEWidget may be nullptr but oldWidget still has\ncomposition since IMEStateManager doesn't guarantee that NOTIFY_IME_OF_BLUR\nis sent after REQUEST_TO_COMMIT_COMPOSITION nor REQUEST_TO_CANCEL_COMPOSITION.\n\nTherefore, when it tries to clean up old widget's composition, it should refer\nthe old widget's IME notification requests.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8kZvJbHfs5z", "files": ["dom/events/IMEStateManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a805179e01649318edd4fb9fe029203241ee25a6", "parents": ["7a6699a52aec8acfd69754f439b6fd0605d827c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387357 - IMContextWrapper::DispatchCompositionStart() should stop dispatching eCompositionStart if dispatching preceding eKeyDown event causes changing active IM context. r=m_kato, a=lizzard\n\nIf a keydown event handler moves focus like Ctrl+PageDown handler, IM context\nmay be changed to DISABLED or something.  In such case, native IME would stop\ncurrent composition because focus moving in Gecko causes making IME blurred.\nHowever, IMContextWrapper::DispatchCompositionStart() always dispatches\neCompositionStart even in such case.\n\nSo, it should stop dispatching eCompositionStart if IME enabled state is\nchanged during dispatching the preceding keydown event.\n\nNote that this patch moves the setter of mComposingContext from\nOnStartCompositionNative() which is a signal listener of \"preedit_start\" to\nDispatchCompositionStart() because if IME starts composition without\n\"preedit_start\" signal, DispatchCompositionStart() will be called but\nOnStartCompositionNative() isn't called.  However, this fix needs\nmComposingContext.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: F3F6NuCOrkJ", "files": ["widget/gtk/IMContextWrapper.cpp", "widget/gtk/IMContextWrapper.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "77d3e7d3c94b3f54cad68887166741823dff01f3", "parents": ["a805179e01649318edd4fb9fe029203241ee25a6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Nguyen \u003ctnguyen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395411 - Unregister tables when they're removed from urlclassifier.*Table. r=francois, a=gchang", "files": ["toolkit/components/url-classifier/SafeBrowsing.jsm", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/nsIUrlListManager.idl", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/nsUrlClassifierListManager.js", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/tests/mochitest/chrome.ini", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/tests/mochitest/test_classifier_changetablepref_bug1395411.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "79c631797f0d12c25c7321805015a45a48efe1dc", "parents": ["77d3e7d3c94b3f54cad68887166741823dff01f3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Cheng \u003cjacheng@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392535 - Update GMP fallback downloader for Widevine 1008 CDM. r=mconley, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Ih0HHP1Sho4", "files": ["toolkit/content/gmp-sources/widevinecdm.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1878b936762cbfad0b7586d5d3db699ad02f28d9", "parents": ["79c631797f0d12c25c7321805015a45a48efe1dc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "steveck-chung \u003cschung@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395519 - [Form Autofill] Keep the original data when record updated via submission. r=lchang, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DkVgOlTqVhH", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillHandler.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillParent.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/ProfileStorage.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/browser/browser.ini", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/browser/browser_update_doorhanger.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/fixtures/autocomplete_simple_basic.html", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_addressRecords.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_onFormSubmitted.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5df6d9e6c8ae7d43f888cf36cd1e23da4a8fb347", "parents": ["1878b936762cbfad0b7586d5d3db699ad02f28d9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504810892, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7725": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395519 - Fix ESLint 'no-undef' failure in browser_update_doorhanger.js. r=MattN, a=bustage", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/test/browser/browser_update_doorhanger.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "12cab10e453ed169bced4af91fb1a17357ffb14e", "parents": ["5df6d9e6c8ae7d43f888cf36cd1e23da4a8fb347"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tobias Schneider \u003cschneider@jancona.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394522 - Null check ref pointers when iterating over intersection observers. r=smaug, a=gchang", "files": ["dom/base/nsDocument.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a36d089f670fe6770114a879b8c77cc7842d6545", "parents": ["12cab10e453ed169bced4af91fb1a17357ffb14e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1369560 - Avoid potentially unsafe snprintf usage in FPSCounter. r=mchang, a=gchang\n\nsnprintf returns the number of bytes it would have written when it runs out of\nspace. This patch makes sure we properly handle this unlikely event in\nFPSCounter. This patch also makes sure we don't print out the contents of an\nuninitialized buffer.", "files": ["gfx/layers/composite/FPSCounter.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d2273fb5bca3b592ef05c8973a9220b58a0545b5", "parents": ["a36d089f670fe6770114a879b8c77cc7842d6545"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nils Ohlmeier [:drno] \u003cdrno@ohlmeier.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1384801 - Improve the sdp base64 parser. r=bwc, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 30e64v5vxo8", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/src/sdp/sipcc/sdp_base64.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5d3cb4a84b47aec394ff250c943d14805268f4e1", "parents": ["d2273fb5bca3b592ef05c8973a9220b58a0545b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Nguyen \u003ctnguyen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394053 - Disable download protection on non-official builds. r=francois, r=gcp, a=lizzard", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/privacy.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/privacy.xul", "browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/tests/browser_security-1.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/tests/browser_security-2.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/security.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/security.xul", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_security.js", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c2643f2df57e0003c999362eef3c7f663388b2c2", "parents": ["5d3cb4a84b47aec394ff250c943d14805268f4e1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Felipe Gomes \u003cfelipc@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397379 - getStringPref in clicktoplay-rollout addon throws for new profiles. r=Gijs, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GN0Cgl3jqK5", "files": ["browser/extensions/clicktoplay-rollout/bootstrap.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "765771f59ef116556ff34b4dcd409c7bd1e990d8", "parents": ["c2643f2df57e0003c999362eef3c7f663388b2c2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kelly \u003cmkelly@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397415 - Sync shield-recipe-client v73 from GitHub (commit e96eea7) to Fx56. r=Gijs, a=lizzard\n\nThis patch includes the following PRs:\n\n- #1002: Fix bug 1393257: Stop in-progress studies when opt-out pref changes.\n  https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1002\n\n- #1024: Bug 1371350: Delay almost all startup tasks until after sessionstore-windows-restored\n  https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1024\n\n- #1029: Fix #856: Add type parameter to preference experiment annotations.\n  https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1029\n\nIt also includes the fix from bug 1392648, which one of the PRs relies upon.", "files": ["browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/lib/AddonStudies.jsm", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/lib/CleanupManager.jsm", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/lib/PreferenceExperiments.jsm", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/lib/RecipeRunner.jsm", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/lib/ShieldPreferences.jsm", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/lib/ShieldRecipeClient.jsm", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser.ini", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_CleanupManager.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_PreferenceExperiments.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_RecipeRunner.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_ShieldPreferences.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_ShieldRecipeClient.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9958b8408817f90eb3f2bf7f7201110b8c151ac7", "parents": ["765771f59ef116556ff34b4dcd409c7bd1e990d8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1276488 - Add diagnostics about Prefs startup failures. r=froydnj, a=lizzard", "files": ["modules/libpref/Preferences.cpp", "modules/libpref/Preferences.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3484d06e80e135e84167fe95f8a42320308a2adc", "parents": ["9958b8408817f90eb3f2bf7f7201110b8c151ac7"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_56_0b10_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_56_0b10_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_56_0b10_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1504813602, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7726": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nbg -\u003e 992ddaf6bb03", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2466f8676845c40d2530e8157c8fb37a7c5b4c73", "parents": ["3484d06e80e135e84167fe95f8a42320308a2adc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504854023, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7727": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nja -\u003e 2ca9b6a11d47\nms -\u003e 0f6f350ca73f", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "313264b0dba54869b9910705b87025812a8465cf", "parents": ["2466f8676845c40d2530e8157c8fb37a7c5b4c73"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504879224, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7728": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump. CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], 