f01d58e60d69ab8352a6bfee9cb3a7f03176e2a4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1504974773, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7731": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nfa -\u003e 20acd3a047bb\nhi-IN -\u003e 627e4866fa52\nms -\u003e fa2110716dd9\nte -\u003e f741cee267aa", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "47a217676e96585fad92152ec0e74061a8a1f5a0", "parents": ["d669c5ad9dd46e446f445991b365ec4a8a03af4f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505023224, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7732": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nzh-TW -\u003e ba77ff66e4c3", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa820231d3a1bad2fd1b5d1e1d571f1ace2a0354", "parents": ["47a217676e96585fad92152ec0e74061a8a1f5a0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505048422, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7733": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\neo -\u003e 6122a702e69e\nfa -\u003e 2efca602a538", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dcaa0dad1d1ecb38a54459b75e3c774042236af8", "parents": ["fa820231d3a1bad2fd1b5d1e1d571f1ace2a0354"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505131223, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7734": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1387678 - Skip all tests in test_shadow_dom.py due to intermittent failures. r=jmaher, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KVJMcZWEW8p", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/unit-tests.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "569c9d764b278a4852f6e6a37abce3d8283675f3", "parents": ["dcaa0dad1d1ecb38a54459b75e3c774042236af8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Geoff Brown \u003cgbrown@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393940 - Skip xpcshell test_proxy_scripts.js on linux for frequent intermittent timeouts. r=mixedpuppy, a=test-only", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-common.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "384d05a526d609508a5a4970e5ebae104cf3fa9b", "parents": ["569c9d764b278a4852f6e6a37abce3d8283675f3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1383499 - Animated PNGs should allocate after-first frames on the heap instead of as volatile buffers on Android. r=tnikkel, a=gchang\n\nAnimated image frames are never actually released to let the OS purge\nthem, because AnimationSurfaceProvider keeps them as RawAccessFrameRef.\nMeanwhile, each volatile buffer on Android needs a file handle to be\nretained for as long as the buffer lives. Given sufficient number of\nanimated image frames, we could easily exhaust the available file\nhandles (which in turn causes many problems). As such on Android we\nshould stick with the heap for animated image frames. On other platforms\nit is better to stay because we will avoid a memset, because the OS will\nzero-fill the requested pages on our behalf.", "files": ["image/imgFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1dea2184e5fcf7d23103c8c7045b9c73a221a65b", "parents": ["384d05a526d609508a5a4970e5ebae104cf3fa9b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391430 - Force heap allocated surfaces for image decoding to use an unaligned stride. r=tnikkel, a=gchang\n\nIn bug 1383499 we fixed the case where on Android, animated images could\nconsume all of the available file handles. This is because each volatile\nbuffer will contain a file handle on Android, and animated images can\ncontain many, many frames. However in doing so we introduced a bug where\nthe stride of replacement surface was aligned to a 16-byte boundary. We\ndo not currently support any stride value but pixel size * image width\nin the image decoding framework. This may be something we correct in the\nfuture but for now, we should just ensure all surfaces follow the\nexpected stride value.", "files": ["image/imgFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e8a9bb8e42a2d062a7359d398191a73066af29b5", "parents": ["1dea2184e5fcf7d23103c8c7045b9c73a221a65b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396570 - Null check getter/setter when JSPROP_GETTER/JSPROP_SETTER is set. r=bholley, f=jandem, a=gchang\n\nThese flags don't guarantee that the getter and setter functions are defined.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GBcoRYoKHqL", "files": ["js/xpconnect/wrappers/XrayWrapper.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "21a6d6d4581987dbea486263716f8ee2b877408e", "parents": ["e8a9bb8e42a2d062a7359d398191a73066af29b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ricky Chien \u003cricky060709@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396583 - Fix wrong tooltip position by wrapping hbox. r=jaws, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1xvD0FEcVxm", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/privacy.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c029dea3522fac9316c3e2fddce00a46c41c4385", "parents": ["21a6d6d4581987dbea486263716f8ee2b877408e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395849 - Fix G.722 audio codec. r=jesup, a=gchang\n\nEven though we were building the G.722 codec, we weren't setting the\ndefines so that it would actually be used.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Dw8l2sYwZFA", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/audio_coding/audio_coding.gypi"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "46f03d8bdc415d569e24330df8250a658286d4f7", "parents": ["c029dea3522fac9316c3e2fddce00a46c41c4385"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396290 - nsStringStream should propagate the OOM error of SetData() when cloned. r=froydnj, a=gchang", "files": ["xpcom/io/nsStringStream.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65dc1a82b406197e52c61f9ae366349f1afb6d39", "parents": ["46f03d8bdc415d569e24330df8250a658286d4f7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388514 - Make the sidebar splitter narrower again to prevent it from overlapping the scrollbar too much, and disable this behavior on Linux since scrollbars are too narrow on Ubuntu. r=Gijs, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Hi4MUsbEFXd", "files": ["browser/themes/linux/browser.css", "browser/themes/shared/sidebar.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5493550a05754ccd38bd90e3d73b58fe3aec14a0", "parents": ["65dc1a82b406197e52c61f9ae366349f1afb6d39"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397711 - Null-check widget of keyboard event before invoking its PostHandleKeyEvent. r=masayuki, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KTniEBMvw9q", "files": ["dom/events/EventStateManager.cpp", "dom/events/crashtests/1397711.html", "dom/events/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e0ce4bfc27efb49056631556f7462b15dc1ca9b4", "parents": ["5493550a05754ccd38bd90e3d73b58fe3aec14a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 791440 - nsGlobalWindow::SetInitialPrincipalToSubject should check the existence of mDoc. r=qdot, a=gchang", "files": ["dom/base/nsGlobalWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d3d0e187d53d5cafeaa050ae1893bc9523e45722", "parents": ["e0ce4bfc27efb49056631556f7462b15dc1ca9b4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505137746, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7735": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nevin Chen \u003ccnevinchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394356 - Temporary remove add to home screen for Android O. r=jwu, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8Uz9QM7i4SD", "files": ["mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-large-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/activitystream_contextmenu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/home_contextmenu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/titlebar_contextmenu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-xlarge-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/delegates/BookmarkStateChangeDelegate.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/promotion/AddToHomeScreenPromotion.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "014826d39b2f14ea1216808d3dde47f043514f05", "parents": ["d3d0e187d53d5cafeaa050ae1893bc9523e45722"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ethan \u003cettseng@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396468 - Spoof navigator.oscpu as 'Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64' when resisting fingerprinting is enabled. r=ehsan, a=gchang", "files": ["browser/components/resistfingerprinting/test/browser/browser_navigator.js", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "715dcb4d80a667dd9c31c2e7bbb4064ba662320c", "parents": ["014826d39b2f14ea1216808d3dde47f043514f05"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shawn Huang \u003cshuang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396300 - Use fallible allocation in GetAsStream. r=bkelly, a=gchang", "files": [