sc": "No bug - Tagging 6bd183fc69218cdbb69a5f9407c69206dade6ae1 with FENNEC_56_0b11_BUILD1, FENNEC_56_0b11_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d44996170d88438d8c38ee7322019ec0f2a5814e", "parents": ["c294885d070fa9ae09ac4827ec7c9e4523d56da6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505235595, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7746": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nevin Chen \u003ccnevinchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394356 - Hide add to home screen option for android O. r=jwu, a=lizzard", "files": ["mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-large-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/activitystream_contextmenu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/home_contextmenu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-v26/titlebar_contextmenu.xml", "mobile/android/app/src/main/res/menu-xlarge-v26/browser_app_menu.xml", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/delegates/BookmarkStateChangeDelegate.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/promotion/AddToHomeScreenPromotion.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ca4f93bbc5e1f5af7036d49d80073841573ede1b", "parents": ["d44996170d88438d8c38ee7322019ec0f2a5814e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Randall Barker \u003crbarker@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396233 - Add toolbar offset to screen location of a11y event so Android can draw the target box in the correct location. r=esawin, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9MN0G7VHGOQ", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoAccessibility.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7f66d28e9dd7e902bb34f9f15f3b6b14704e3410", "parents": ["ca4f93bbc5e1f5af7036d49d80073841573ede1b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Grigory Kruglov \u003cgkruglov@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335110 - Catch security exceptions while getting a GCM token to fail gracefully. r=eoger, a=gchang\n\nException handling upstream is already in place, and will ensure that we degrade gracefully.\nPush won't work, but we won't crash either.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EfDNoJu46zg", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/gcm/GcmTokenClient.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ae9c15bff40edd55d76b7a9b094b7a52a7f803d0", "parents": ["7f66d28e9dd7e902bb34f9f15f3b6b14704e3410"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505236296, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7747": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nms -\u003e 6b24e1c11c0a\ntr -\u003e 921c1b013006", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ee35e197066d9c09218bd26f4d0ec72faa9fac6a", "parents": ["ae9c15bff40edd55d76b7a9b094b7a52a7f803d0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505246422, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7748": {"changesets": [{"author": "jason laster \u003cjlaster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398893 - Breakpoints cannot be removed. r=jdescottes, a=lizzard", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/new/debugger.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cdfda62c6effbb46b3b1bcd2f92dccf642881647", "parents": ["ee35e197066d9c09218bd26f4d0ec72faa9fac6a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Zibi Braniecki \u003czbraniecki@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397925 - Refresh OSPreferences mSystemLocales when intl.locale.os changes. r=rnewman, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: oJdWUXwhZw", "files": ["intl/locale/LocaleService.cpp", "intl/locale/OSPreferences.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa3740564226ff05000c83f7b07a919334bd7ac1", "parents": ["cdfda62c6effbb46b3b1bcd2f92dccf642881647"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1385630 - Fix extension sidebar restore after app update. r=Gijs, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IR0UDJgrp58", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-sidebar.js", "browser/components/extensions/ext-sidebarAction.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bb89faa93b22a12c442275cb1ec0d2d6a1f0d800", "parents": ["aa3740564226ff05000c83f7b07a919334bd7ac1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Stenberg \u003cdaniel@haxx.se\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1359624 - Disable nsAuthSambaNTLM module on OSX. r=mayhemer, a=lizzard", "files": ["extensions/auth/nsAuthFactory.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bd8b51b807381ceef0dd12aa0534b65bf6e12f3d", "parents": ["bb89faa93b22a12c442275cb1ec0d2d6a1f0d800"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Steve Fink \u003csfink@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1389974 - \"Fix\" false positive rooting hazard in ArrayInfo(). r=jonco, a=lizzard\n\nA hazard is reported where on one iteration through the loop over the arguments, obj is set to a JSObject*. Then on the next iteration, the analysis incorrectly things that the if test could skip overwriting obj, and instead call as() on the previous iteration's value. This turns out to be impossible because reaching as() requires the if condition to be false, which means that both branches of the or are evaluated, and the second branch assigns to obj.\n\nIt seems like the call to as() should be dominated by the obj assignment, but in practice the compiler assigns to a temporary boolean variable and then tests it, so in terms of control flow only the as() call is *not* dominated by the obj assignment.\n\nThis patch just roots obj.\n***\nBug 1389974 - Avoid taking reference to temporary Value because it hides from hazard analysis, r=jonco\n***\nBug 1389974 - Rooting fixes for nsJSNPRuntime.cpp, r=froydnj\n***\nBug 1389974 - Annotate nsIScriptSecurityManager.IsSystemPrincipal, r=jonco\n***\nBug 1389974 - Do not require ffi_call to exist, r=jonco\n***\nBug 1389974 - Remove the implication that killing a value overrides using it, r=bhackett", "files": ["dom/plugins/base/nsJSNPRuntime.cpp", "js/src/devtools/rootAnalysis/analyzeRoots.js", "js/src/devtools/rootAnalysis/annotations.js", "js/src/devtools/rootAnalysis/loadCallgraph.js", "js/src/devtools/rootAnalysis/t/hazards/source.cpp", "js/src/devtools/rootAnalysis/t/hazards/test.py", "js/src/jsarray.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b55ee75e7abac770cc7b235aa1e05a28672e0433", "parents": ["bd8b51b807381ceef0dd12aa0534b65bf6e12f3d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334582 - Use UINT64_MAX instead of IsInfinite() for checking whether TimingParans.mIterations is infinite or not. r=boris, a=lizzard\n\nBecause our ComputedTiming.mCurrentIteration is uint64_t.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FjbhEvTUMr4", "files": ["dom/animation/AnimationEffectReadOnly.cpp", "dom/animation/test/crashtests/1334582-1.html", "dom/animation/test/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e35824dc078285160f59b2f5d3ad2f2cc12168b2", "parents": ["b55ee75e7abac770cc7b235aa1e05a28672e0433"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334582 - Check whether overall progress exceeds UINT64_MAX. r=boris, a=lizzard\n\nThe overall progress is factored in iteration start, so even if\nTimingParams.mIterations is less than UINT64_MAX, it will exceed UINT64_MAX.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CEOYAGsCoIE", "files": ["dom/animation/AnimationEffectReadOnly.cpp", "dom/animation/test/crashtests/1334582-2.html", "dom/animation/test/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a18761befb035cddbf8c48644254b0a909719870", "parents": ["e35824dc078285160f59b2f5d3ad2f2cc12168b2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Richard Newman \u003crnewman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1378501 - Tell Gecko when the OS locale changes, even when backgrounded. r=mcomella, a=lizzard\n\nThis ensures that `intl.locale.os` is always set, even if the system locale changes\nwhile Fennec is in the background.\n\nThis commit also restores `Strings.flush()` calls that are necessary to have Fennec's\nnon-Java UI reflect locale changes.\n\nWith this commit, the geolocation popup still doesn't behave correctly: when the\nlocale system is set to match OS locale, although the pref is set the locale doesn't\nchange. This applies in two scenarios: on first run (the popup is always English)\nand when the locale changes at runtime (the popup uses an earlier OS locale).\n\nBug 1397925 should complete the fix.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8zeZuYXFYdy", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserLocaleManager.java", "mobile/android/chrome/content/browser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "867b9e3b4f92445085c77cecf485f6a5568faeaf", "parents": ["a18761befb035cddbf8c48644254b0a909719870"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505264344, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7749": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nkn -\u003e 55759b14a854\nlo -\u003e 8f5607f1c691", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b18db107cfb866c71158d485ac4c905352758e5", "parents": ["867b9e3b4f92445085c77cecf485f6a5568faeaf"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505293222, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7750": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nkn -\u003e 31ae580f21d7\nms -\u003e a484e345b13b", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "be059eaafd1a908cc9a57f5b93a2f0f258c73f7a", "parents": ["3b18db107cfb866c71158d485ac4c905352758e5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505300423, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7751": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nast -\u003e 9a0f43b5531a", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "606b48a1cd7a45cb62069ee0cf5a2e756fbb6a29", "parents": ["be059eaafd1a908cc9a57f5b93a2f0f258c73f7a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505307621, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "7752": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ho-Pang Hsu \u003chopang.hsu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1379200 - Preserve the precision of a timestamp when converting it to string. r=bkelly, a=test-only", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/resources/bytecheck-worker-imported-script.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/resources/bytecheck-worker.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc985a161026f2e0ddeaf9b31c54d98226182c05", "parents": ["606b48a1cd7a45cb62069ee0cf5a2e756fbb6a29"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Peter Van der Beken \u003cpeterv@propagandism.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391118 - xslt-generated select tag pull-down does not respond to clicks. r=jaws, a=lizzard", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/forms/browser_selectpopup.js", "toolkit/modules/SelectContentHelper.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d087540c96b5da7417824dcb6ae7014594f20d94", "parents": ["fc985a161026f2e0ddeaf9b31c54d98226182c05"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Odvarko \u003codvarko@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396811 - Add new telemetry probe collecting the current theme. r=chutten,liuche,ochameau, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KlUHlc7YEx9", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/toolbox.js", "devtools/client/shared/telemetry.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6c62bfeef4a8671053ddc9b074664d5eb4e6b3f1", "parents": ["d087540c96b5da7417824dcb6ae7014594f20d94"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392202 - WebSocket CTOR should not try to look for the topmost window if the opener's top ancestor is equal to the current window top ancestor. r=smaug, a=lizzard", "files": ["dom/base/WebSocket.cpp", "dom/base/test/frame_bug1384658.html", "dom/base/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/base/test/test_bug1384658.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a085ae94f23a9d659ae09602018a52857ebde86f", "parents": ["6c62bfeef4a8671053ddc9b074664d5eb4e6b3f1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505317194, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7753": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392210 - Follow-up: Fix missing Services.jsm import. r=trivial, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9YqoYN5yAIe", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ext-browser-content.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a923590e3e1c97b7b982f8a17c1a65b1ebb8cbc", "parents": ["a085ae94f23a9d659ae09602018a52857ebde86f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399599 - Disable speculative connections from the Address Bar in Firefox 56. r=ryanvm, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7FcMOTROZ67", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f5502ee28a5037600a2989a355ecf0ef743ccdf1", "parents": ["4a923590e3e1c97b7b982f8a17c1a65b1ebb8cbc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kaku Kuo \u003ckaku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388309 - Let VideoDecoderChild::InitIPDL() return false if we don't want to decode video on GPU process. r=mattwoodrow, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DD7xVkXT6fk", "files": ["dom/media/ipc/VideoDecoderChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3de2b4f255b3b6284b8a28cfe2cf5a88863f8d3b", "parents": ["f5502ee28a5037600a2989a355ecf0ef743ccdf1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Steve Chung \u003cschung@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1341569 - Add the form created time in handler and telemetry probe for form filling duration. r=MattN, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DDXBkoEUT7v", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillContent.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillHandler.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillParent.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "32ed0185f6ed285dbf6cc1903d0d3759a190c134", "parents": ["3de2b4f255b3b6284b8a28cfe2cf5a88863f8d3b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391186 - Thunderbird loses setting as default email client when \"mailto\" triggered by Firefox 56/57 (OS X 10.11). r=spohl, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: H0VVoHR7LmQ", "files": ["uriloader/exthandler/mac/nsOSHelperAppService.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5c273f80b63f63c38ee60fc11710af5b2b4fdc42", "parents": ["32ed0185f6ed285dbf6cc1903d0d3759a190c134"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1393687 - Use VideoAdapter to handle max-fs. r=jesup, a=lizzard\n\nThis uses the VideoAdapter to handle the max-fs constraint rather than\nattempting to calculate and enforce it manually within the VideoConduit.\nThe resolution is taken as the small of the max-fs constraint and the\nlatest request from the video sink.\n\nThe old unit tests for max-fs and max-fr are removed as the size\ncalculation has now been delegated to the VideoAdapter and the tests do\nnot verify whether or not video has actually been scaled.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 18khmiNageR", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/gtest/mediaconduit_unittests.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/MediaConduitInterface.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/VideoConduit.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/VideoConduit.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9cc3488283435107d323374e119b195c3dd3f851", "parents": ["5c273f80b63f63c38ee60fc11710af5b2b4fdc42"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Doug Thayer \u003cdothayer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399172 - Add buttonhighlight to update doorhangers. r=johannh, a=lizzard\n\nThe highlight styling was recently added, causing update notification\nbuttons to both be styled as grey. This fixes that to style them as\nblue again.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HDSA9NWBmIA", "files": ["browser/components/customizableui/content/panelUI.inc.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "88a62be317eef6751439d3856b54b50ff894d0ad", "parents": ["9cc3488283435107d323374e119b195c3dd3f851"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Doug Thayer \u003cdothayer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399172 - Add highlight styling to Flash notification. r=johannh, a=lizzard\n\nThe Flash (plugin) notification buttons have been restyled\ntemporarily to make them in line with other doorhangers. There\nis further work being done to use PopupNotifications.jsm fully\nfor these notifications, rather than PopupNotifications + a custom\nXBL binding. However, this won't make it for 57, so this change\nfixes the temporary restyle to ensure that the default button\nis blue.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FSlmOdLd8SW", "files": ["browser/base/content/urlbarBindings.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a0d1ab4aa8c237d91c38729a401ecb1dd098fcd1", "parents": ["88a62be317eef6751439d3856b54b50ff894d0ad"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505336004, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7754": {"changesets": [{"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1385239 - Part 1: Pass gfxContext, instead of DrawTarget, into nsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame. r=mstange, a=lizzard\n\nThis change makes the next patch free of doing Matrix to gfxMatrix conversion.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8K9RNgjZPTw", "files": ["layout/svg/nsFilterInstance.cpp", "layout/svg/nsFilterInstance.h", "layout/svg/nsSVGIntegrationUtils.cpp", "layout/svg/nsSVGUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b663bd73db28c0ea8613940369f96996f34d6aca", "parents": ["a0d1ab4aa8c237d91c38729a401ecb1dd098fcd1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1385239 - Part 2: Remove aTransform parameter from PaintFilteredFrame. r=mstange, a=lizzard\n\nThere are two callers of nsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame:\n1. nsSVGUtils::PaintFrameWithEffects at [1]\n   This function is used while painting a filtered element on a path which\n   display item painting is not supported yet, such as drawing elements inside a\n   indirect painted SVG object, such as a mask, a clipPath or a gradient object.\n\n   Let's say we have a masked element, which refers to an SVG mask, and there is\n   a filtered element inside that SVG mask.\n   Using nsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame to paint that filtered frame in\n   the mask, we have to pass a gfxContext and a transform matrix to it. The\n   transform of the gfxContext 'target' that we pass in consists of a transform\n   from the referenced frame, of the masked frame, to the masked frame. We also\n   pass in a transform matrix 'aTransform', this matrix contains a transform\n   from the the masked frame to the filtered frame in *device units*, which\n   means it contains css-to-dev-px scaling factor.\n\n2. nsSVGIntegrationUtils::PaintFilter at [2]\n   This function is used by normal display item painting.\n\n   The same, we pass a gfxContext 'context' and a transform matrix 'tm' into\n   nsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame. The transform matrix of 'context'\n   consists of a transform from the referenced frame, of the filtered frame,\n   to this filtered frame, but the scale factor was taken out . The transform\n   matrix 'tm' we pass in contains scale transform from the referenced frame to\n   the filtered frame in *device unit*.\n\nInside nsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame, we treat the transform matrix of\n'aCtx' and 'aTransform' as parameters we pass in in #2 caller. So it can be\nfailed in #1. For example, if the filtered frame inside a masked frame has a\ntranslation transform applied, since that translation was put in 'aTransfrom',\nbut we only use the scale factor of 'aTransform' in\nnsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame, translation factor disappears.\n\nIn this patch, I unified the definition of parameters of\nnsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame:\n1. nsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame(aCtx): the transform matrix of aCtx\n   should be a transform from the referenced frame to the filtered frame in\n   *css units*. Originally, the aCtx we passed in #1 is in device units, which\n   should be fixed; the aCtx we passed in #2 does not even include css scaling\n   factor, need be fixed too.\n2. nsFilterInstance::PaintFilteredFrame(aTransform): this transform matrix\n   should contain only scaling factor in device units. And I removed it in the\n   end since I found we can get this value easily right inside the callee.\n\n[1]\nhttps://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/file/ef585ac7c476/layout/svg/nsSVGUtils.cpp#l857\n\n[2]\nhttps://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/file/ef585ac7c476/layout/svg/nsSVGIntegrationUtils.cpp#l1114\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: gRV128NyQv", "files": ["layout/svg/nsFilterInstance.cpp", "layout/svg/nsFilterInstance.h", "layout/svg/nsSVGIntegrationUtils.cpp", "layout/svg/nsSVGUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "45497624d7928fbd67eb09a8a682ce255e273d22", "parents": ["b663bd73db28c0ea8613940369f96996f34d6aca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1385239 - Part 3: A test case of putting a translated filtered element inside an SVG mask. r=mstange, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AqSL8Gb5R46", "files": ["layout/reftests/svg/filters/filter-in-mask-01.svg", "layout/reftests/svg/filters/filter-in-mask-02.svg", "layout/reftests/svg/filters/filter-in-mask.svg", "layout/reftests/svg/filters/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "acd7c5826e6ac0f3a323d3b35034b13538ecdc4b", "parents": ["45497624d7928fbd67eb09a8a682ce255e273d22"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexander Surkov \u003csurkov.alexander@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1368269 - Crash in mozilla::a11y::XULTreeAccessible::Shutdown. r=marcoz, a=lizzard", "files": ["accessible/xul/XULTreeAccessible.cpp", "accessible/xul/XULTreeGridAccessible.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d0a01370e594f7f793d5dc4d2589b7a24f9b8ca4", "parents": ["acd7c5826e6ac0f3a323d3b35034b13538ecdc4b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Zibi Braniecki \u003czbraniecki@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1386015 - Do not generate styling for each element with inherited color. r=jaws, a=lizzard\n\nThis patch does a minor refactor of the code used to style popup menu for\nthe \u003cselect\u003e element.\nIt improves the custom styling experience on MacOS, preserves the functionality\non Windows and removes the unnecessary per-item CSS rules significantly\nimproving the performance of opening the \u003cselect\u003e list.\n\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7myXq8aDAWr", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/forms/browser_selectpopup_colors.js", "toolkit/modules/SelectParentHelper.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5c43034960096da09592861b4ad7d2ddb344d8e1", "parents": ["d0a01370e594f7f793d5dc4d2589b7a24f9b8ca4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ricky Chien \u003cricky060709@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397723 - Correct Preferences search matching approach for search feature. r=mconley, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1t8oXYvwHbl", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/findInPage.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/main.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8850107a6a8b5e124c86a2e1bedbcc4f01ac43f9", "parents": ["5c43034960096da09592861b4ad7d2ddb344d8e1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ricky Chien \u003cricky060709@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397731 - Clear Preferences search query after category switchover. r=mconley, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DoV5xHW0xKP", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/preferences.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b0f08e34f67d602245dae02dc534bf9aee2ba7fd", "parents": ["8850107a6a8b5e124c86a2e1bedbcc4f01ac43f9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505340479, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7755": {"changesets": [{"author": "Luke Chang \u003clchang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1382548 - [Form Autofill] Avoid sending element references in messages. r=ralin, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: F6EXJl9dl8s", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillContent.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "577b2db694a7812dd737c4e18283119c53277630", "parents": ["b0f08e34f67d602245dae02dc534bf9aee2ba7fd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ricky Chien \u003cricky060709@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397729 - Strings inside cookies dialog are not found when searched. r=mconley, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6LOE6aBZX0J", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/privacy.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/privacy.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6bc1744c12eed8c652ca811053e8ce859c2c4a1c", "parents": ["577b2db694a7812dd737c4e18283119c53277630"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395898 - Awesome Screenshot webextension does not work. r=jimm, a=lizzard\n\nFix ExtensionProtocolHandler::GetAsync() to handle failures returned\nfrom AsyncOpen2() for cached JAR resources.\n\nDon't call SetupEventTarget() in the cached JAR ExtensionStreamGetter\nconstructor because the event target is not needed and calling\nSetupEventTarget() triggers a debug mode warning from\nnsContentUtils::GetEventTargetByLoadInfo().\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KjDsPNQWlwU", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "58e1249a4920875a7935730b61b788dc3d7288ff", "parents": ["6bc1744c12eed8c652ca811053e8ce859c2c4a1c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397257 - [Windows] Awesome Screenshot removing error for a second uninstallation. r=jimm, a=lizzard\n\nFix circular dependency created when encountering a path to a nonexistent JAR\ninner file.\n\nChange cache JAR loads to not use ExtensionStreamGetter, instead call the JAR\nchannel's AsyncOpen2 method directly in the SimpleChannel callback.\nRemove the code to handle cached JAR loads from ExtensionStreamGetter.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Kmry02eLYU1", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fafd69ca273333772746a9c54ec7975a6ab1bc42", "parents": ["58e1249a4920875a7935730b61b788dc3d7288ff"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505342729, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7756": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 5c4303496009 (bug 1386015) for browser_selectpopup_colors.js failures.", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/forms/browser_selectpopup_colors.js", "toolkit/modules/SelectParentHelper.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "776744d895c98d89764bca8018509a77a2127cab", "parents": ["fafd69ca273333772746a9c54ec7975a6ab1bc42"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398622 - Fix ws handling in contentpolicymanager, and fix stupid error. r=kmag, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EmPvtRrnrnI", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/mochitest/test_ext_webrequest_websocket.html", "toolkit/modules/addons/WebRequest.jsm", "toolkit/modules/addons/WebRequestContent.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1aadca44c4b72c06d18fc046b85444fc411d4980", "parents": ["776744d895c98d89764bca8018509a77a2127cab"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1352016 - Disable NV12 D3D11 surfaces. r=mattwoodrow, a=lizzard\n\nNV12 causes issue with older nvidia and AMD cards.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KXMjZVLXNg5", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e8e660d7c455191c250bbb728e97e411c42a4338", "parents": ["1aadca44c4b72c06d18fc046b85444fc411d4980"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 6bc1744c12ee (bug 1397729) for multiple browser-chrome failures.", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/privacy.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/privacy.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "15c749b4b2646adf948c09645b1e9ce4f83a2b03", "parents": ["e8e660d7c455191c250bbb728e97e411c42a4338"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ricky Chien \u003cricky060709@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397729 - Strings inside cookies dialog are not found when searched. r=mconley, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6LOE6aBZX0J", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/privacy.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content-new/privacy.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e342ff01ad5566180910859946df3ea792279239", "parents": ["15c749b4b2646adf948c09645b1e9ce4f83a2b03"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Scott Wu \u003cscottcwwu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1386922 - Add learn more link to autofill address. r=lchang, r=MattN, a=lizzard, l10n=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LloJRy8srb1", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillPreferences.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/locales/en-US/formautofill.properties", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/browser/browser_privacyPreferences.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "faf98f63da30ed2715f6a51d45cbc84dd76efeb4", "parents": ["e342ff01ad5566180910859946df3ea792279239"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505348728, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7757": {"changesets": [{"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398622 - Followup patch to fix beta difference from m-c. r=kmag, a=bustage", "files": ["toolkit/modules/addons/WebRequest.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fbef00b40b98333a637211cd284db9e3f5348f07", "parents": ["faf98f63da30ed2715f6a51d45cbc84dd76efeb4"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_56_0b12_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_56_0b12_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_56_0b12_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1505357311, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "7758": {"changesets": [{"author": "Luke Chang \u003clchang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1391149 - [Form Autofill] Avoid exposing fields with empty value from the storage. r=steveck a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8WHCFNNckO4", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/ProfileStorage.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_transformFields.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1c08a2f4d2fc14e2a88915a2bd8f033f04c058ab", "parents": ["fbef00b40b98333a637211cd284db9e3f5348f07"], "tags": []}], "date": 1505372936, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kwierso@gmail.com"}, "7759": {"changesets": [{"author": "Luke Chang \u003clchang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392975 - [Form Autofill] Avoid registering multiple listeners of DOMContentLoaded. r=seanlee a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Eo3KSBoaotr\n---\n .../formautofill/FormAutofillContent.jsm           | 27 ++++------\n .../extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillUtils.jsm  | 11 +++-\n .../content/FormAutofillFrameScript.js             | 61 +++++++++++++---------\n 3 files changed, 56 insertions(+), 43 deletions(-)", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillContent.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillUtils.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/content/FormAutofillFrameScript.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "12809a8ce21a7b10c7a4e54baa9ae742c176de87", "parents": ["1c08a2f4d2fc14e2a88915a2bd8f033f04c058ab"], "tags": ["FIREFOX_RELEASE_56_BASE"]}], "date": 1505376810, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "7760": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging mozilla-beta 12809a8ce21a7b10c7a4e54baa9ae742c176de87 with FIREFOX_RELEASE_56_BASE a=release DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d519209bdd0a4dd4c4a74f0a9097851d949eb25f", "parents": ["12809a8ce21a7b10c7a4e54baa9ae742c176de87"], "tags": ["FIREFOX_BETA_56_END"]}], "date": 1505397635, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "sfraser@mozilla.com"}}
}";